title: surprise pork
directions: For Grill-Indirect.
In oven, 400° for 1 hour.

title: margaritas
directions: Cut lime in half.
Rub rims of glasses with lime.
Dip rims in salt and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender.
Pour into glasses.
Makes 6 (5 ounce) servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts, tear them apart and mash. Combine all other ingredients. Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly around the edges.

title: coconut pecan topping
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine Eagle Brand milk, egg yolks and Crisco; over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Stir in coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Cool.

title: kraut relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving.
Yields 1 quart.

title: whole wheat zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour three 7 1/2 x 3 1/4 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pans; set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine flours, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat eggs, sugar and oil at medium speed until fluffy.
With a spoon, stir in zucchini.
Add dry ingredients to egg-zucchini mixture, stirring just until flour is moistened.
Pour into prepared pans and bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until tests done.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool on wire racks.
When cool, wrap in foil and refrigerate. Slice and serve the following day.

title: green chili stew
directions: Cut meat into 3-inch chunks and rub with chili, cumin and oregano.
Heat oil in 5-quart pot and brown meat.
Remove meat and saute onion.
Stir in garlic, stock and bay leaf.
Put meat back in and simmer 30 minutes.

title: orange roughy with sauteed garden vegetables
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Coat each fillet with melted margarine and place in baking dish.
Place fish fillets in preheated 350° oven and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, gently saute dill weed, peppers, tomatoes and onion until tender.
After fish is baked, top with sauteed vegetables.
Add bread crumbs to skillet and brown slightly.
Sprinkle over top of fish and vegetables.
Serve immediately with rice and vegetables.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out flat in a large jelly roll pan. Press crescent rolls with fingers to fit pan.
Bake crescent rolls in oven at 375° for approximately 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions. Brown ground beef in heavy skillet (drain fat). Add corn, mushroom soup, tomato soup, salt and chili powder. Drain noodles and add to meat mixture. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until mixture is bubbly and cheese has melted.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix together.
Cook
over
low	heat between medium and low, until thick,
about 2 hours.
Stir often.
Pour into jars while hot and seal.

title: crab dip
directions: Stir together soup mix, sour cream and lemon juice.
Stir in drained crabmeat, drained and chopped artichoke hearts, shredded Swiss cheese and dill weed.
Cover.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Makes 3 3/4 cups.
Serve with crackers.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Drain shrimp and save liquid in bowl.
Cook macaroni and drain with cold water.
Break up and add shrimp.
Add pickles cut in small pieces.
Add chopped celery and sprinkle with garlic salt. Mix.
Put 1 cup salad dressing into a separate bowl.
Slowly add French dressing, mixing well.
Add shrimp liquid and mix.
Add to large bowl and mix.
Sprinkle parsley flakes over the top and chill.

title: thanksgiving pie
directions: Crust:
Take one measure of thankfulness and thoroughly sift out all lumps of sin and selfishness with a Calvary sieve.*
Add one heaping measure of patience and moisten with the water of God's Word until dough is pliable enough to stretch without tearing.
Fit into heart-shaped container and bake at highest heat until very firm.
Then fill with the following:

title: berry syrup
directions: In a 2 qt. saucepan, combine berries, water and sugar.
If the berries are big, cut them up first.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat; stirring occasionally to prevent it from scorching to the bottom of the pan.
Reduce heat and simmer for five minutes.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Store in a glass canning jar in fridge.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Form into a ball and roll in pecans.
Chill.

title: raspberry applesauce salad
directions: Combine sour cream and marshmallows.
Cover; store in refrigerator.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups of water.
Add the frozen raspberries (juice, too) and the applesauce.
After this is set, whip the sour cream-marshmallow mixture until it is spreading consistency.
Spread over jello.

title: chocolate butter frosting
directions: Melt chocolate and blend with vanilla, if using squares.
If using cocoa, sift with confectioners sugar.
Mix ingredients together.
Add milk if needed to make of spreading consistency.

title: corned beef sandwich spread
directions: Grind onion and bell pepper in blender, or chop very fine. Heat corned beef just lukewarm.
Mix onion, pepper and corned beef.
Add mayonnaise to make spreading consistency.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spread on bread of your choice.

title: grilled oysters
directions: Combine melted butter, onion, garlic, lemon pepper and parsley. Fill muffin tin 1/3 full with onion mixture and top with large oyster or 2 small ones.
Place muffin tins on grill and cook 5 to 10 minutes or until oysters turn white and barely curl at edges. Good hors d'oeuvre when cooking on grill.

title: dog food
directions: Melt chocolate chips, oleo and peanut butter.
Toss in cereal; shake in bag with 2 cups powdered sugar.
Let cool on cookie sheet.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together and make into 1-inch balls.
Brown in 3 tablespoons hot oil.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Wash eggplant and slice about 1/4-inch thick.
Beat 2 eggs in bowl.
In another bowl, put flour and paprika; mix well.
In skillet, put enough cooking oil to cover eggplant.
Dip eggplant in egg and then in flour mixture and fry until lightly browned on both sides.
Layer in shallow baking dish as follows:
layer of browned eggplant, cover with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with grated cheese, parsley and basil.
Pour tomato sauce over this.
Layer again in same order.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix. Simmer 5 minutes.
Press dough onto bottom of ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan, pressing edges together to form seal.
Prick bottom with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cover with meat mixture; top with cheese slices.
Continue baking until cheese begins to melt.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with sour cream if desired.

title: macaroni, sausage and broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on the box.
Add remaining ingredients to macaroni and cheese.
Mix well.
Bake in a casserole dish for 45 minutes in a 350° oven or until thoroughly heated.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Put bread cubes in melted margarine; stir until brown.
Mix sugar and flour together, then add pineapple.
Add eggs and stir well.
Place browned bread cubes on pineapple mixture in alternate layers in casserole.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Delicious warm or cold, especially good with baked ham.

title: iowa pork chops
directions: Sprinkle 1 teaspoon salt on pork chops and brown them in the shortening in a skillet.
Transfer to casserole dish (along with pan drippings).
Mix together other ingredients and add to dish. Cover dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover dish and continue to bake for approximately another 1/2 hour and then enjoy an Iowa pork chop dinner.

title: cookie casserole(frozen)
directions: Crush 3 1/2 rows cookies in food processor and reserve handful to sprinkle on top.
Spray Pam in a 9 x 13-inch glass Pyrex dish. Flatten the crushed cookies in the dish and up the sides.
Drizzle oleo over this and freeze.
Smooth softened ice cream over this for the next layer.
Pour caramel over the ice cream layer and put Cool Whip on top.
Drizzle cookie crumbs and leftover caramel on top.
Cover with Saran Wrap and freeze.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate pie from scratch
directions: Mix dry ingredients, plus egg yolks together.
Get milk real hot; do not scorch.
While milk is heating, take 1/2 cup and add to the dry mixture.
Add slowly to the milk, while stirring continuously, until thickens and bubbles.
Add margarine and stir until it melts.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream peanut butter, sugar, margarine and vanilla together with hands.
After it is mixed well, shape into buckeye size balls.
Melt chocolate bits and paraffin in a double boiler (3/4 inch water).
After melting, use a toothpick to dip balls into chocolate, a little over halfway in.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Cut biscuits in half and coat in sugar mixture.
Lay into greased Bundt pan.
Mix remaining sugar mixture with melted butter and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white sheet cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and egg whites until fluffy.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until springs back.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix.
Will be stiff like play doh.
If too dry, add applesauce.
If too moist, add cinnamon.
Roll 1/4-inch thick (easier if done between 2 sheets wax paper with cinnamon).
Cut out with cookie cutters.
Poke a hole with a straw near the top. Lay flat on brown bags.
Let dry 4 to 5 days until completely dry.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix and bake as directed on box in angel food cake pan.

title: mulled cider
directions: Tie whole spices in cheesecloth bag.
Drop bag into kettle of hot cider with sugar added and let it simmer until cider is spicy enough.
Serve in mugs with dash of nutmeg.
Serves 6.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, put a layer of meat, then Tater Tots, cheese and 1/2 can of the soup.
Repeat layers.
Cover dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Add sugar, butter, vinegar and vanilla; continue whipping with fork and add coconut.
Pour into unbaked crust; bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: festive chicken
directions: Wrap 2 bacon strips around each chicken breast; place in a shallow glass baking dish and set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, combine soy sauce and sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken, turning to coat evenly.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix together and heat.

title: cheese delights
directions: Cream together cheese and butter.
Blend in flour and salt. Form in balls about the size of marbles.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten down with fork to make a waffle design. Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Chill for several hours in refrigerator.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until browned.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch and water.
Boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in slightly beaten egg yolks.
Return to low heat; cook for 6 minutes.
Add butter, lemon juice and grated peel; stir only until well blended. Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff; add remaining sugar and vanilla.
Beat until firm peaks form; spread over lemon filling.
Bake at 325° to 350° until meringue is lightly browned.

title: tagliarini casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Cook egg noodles and drain. In a 9 x 13 baking pan, place ground beef in bottom of dish, then pour tomato sauce evenly over beef. Then add egg noodles, then creamed corn, then mushrooms and then cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and slightly browned. Serve with salad and bread. Enjoy!

title: fruit crunch
directions: Mix together egg, flour and sugar; it will be crumbly.
In a deep 9-inch pie pan, grease or spray with Pam.
Put pie filling of your choice in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle crumbly mixture on top of this.
Melt butter and drizzle on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zesty stuffed tomatoes
directions: Scoop out tomatoes and turn upside down on paper towels.
A 1/4 teaspoon measuring spoon is perfect.
In small bowl, combine sour cream, peppers, onions, flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well. Using a pastry bag or small spoon, fill each tomato (can be done up to 8 hours ahead) and place on foil-lined pan.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes or until sour cream is bubbly.
Sprinkle with cheese and broil 2 to 3 minutes longer until cheese is melted.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
A blender works great!
Chill to blend flavors.
Will keep for weeks in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti goulash
directions: Brown onion in fat.
Add green pepper and celery, chopped; cover and cook until well wilted.
Pour over spaghetti which has been cooked.
Place meat in skillet and brown meat.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes; mix with spaghetti mixture and pour into a large casserole.
Cover with tomato soup and grate cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let set for 20 minutes.
Roll out flat.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Drop in hot chicken broth.

title: seaside shell salad(say this 3 times fast!)
directions: Boil shells, drain and rinse.
In food processor, chop onion, green pepper, carrot, celery and tuna.
(If using water packed tuna, add a little olive oil to mixture, not much, a tablespoon or so.)

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add egg and flavorings.
Mix thoroughly.
Measure flour after sifting.
Sift in flour and cream of tartar.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Roll out and cut into shapes. Bake for 6 to 8 minutes on greased cookie sheet in a 350° oven.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs.
Beat until mixture is stiff.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add enough milk to fill freezer.
Freeze according to ice cream freezer directions.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together cheeses, add onion and some pecans.
Chill, form into ball and press remaining pecan pieces onto ball.

title: a really good punch
directions: Mix together and use water to own taste.
Use ice cubes and/or frozen ring.

title: cheddar soup
directions: Cook vegetables in boiling water until tender; do not drain. Melt butter.
Add flour; cook about 2 minutes.
Add milk and broth.
Cook until thick.
Add cheese; stir to melt.
Add vegetables in water.
Stir until smooth.

title: apple-oatmeal bars
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,
except
apple,
together
with electric
mixer
until
smooth.
Add apple; beat a few seconds more.
Pour batter into Pam sprayed 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into 24 bars.
Recipe equals: 2 protein units, 3 dairy units, 2 grain and 1 fruit unit.

title: ri's chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a large 3 1/2 to 4-quart casserole, melt margarine.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place hamburger over bottom of baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle chopped onion over meat.
Pour cans of soup over hamburger, then the drained peas.
Place Tater Tots (frozen) over the top.
Bake for 1 hour, or until done, at 350°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix
cake according to directions and cook in rectangular pan.
While
still hot, punch holes in cake and pour milk all over top.
When cool, spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with coconut.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: In a heavy Dutch oven, melt the bacon grease.
Add smoked sausage pieces, onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook until vegetables wilt.
Add chicken broth, bay leaf, thyme, allspice, parsley, poultry seasoning, red pepper, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer the mixture for 30 minutes.
Add 2 cans of cream of chicken soup and cooked rice.
Toss mixture until rice is hot.
Add the 2 cans of chicken breast.
This can be placed on top of rice mixture or mixed into rice.
Cover and place in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix molasses and boiling water; add baking soda.
Then mix flour, oil or shortening, salt and brown sugar.
Mix until crumbly.
Take out 1 3/4 cups for top of cake.
Then mix remaining crumbs with liquid.
Pour into ungreased cake pan.
Sprinkle 1 3/4 cups on top.

title: appetizer cut-outs
directions: Unfold pie crusts; cut out with 2 1/2 inch cutters.
Place cut-outs on ungreased cookie sheet; prick each several times with fork.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown; cool.
Combine cream cheese, milk, onion salt and Worcestershire sauce, mixing until blended.
Spread on cut-outs.
Top with remaining ingredients, as desired.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: easy pork and rice
directions: Brown meat lightly in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Add rice and cook 15 minutes longer or until rice is tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: yulekaje - christmas fruit bread
directions: Pour scalded milk over sugar, salt and oleo. Cool until lukewarm. Add the well beaten eggs, then add ground cardamon. Sprinkle the yeast over the warm water and sugar. Allow yeast to dissolve for 5 minutes in warm water and sugar. Add yeast to cool milk mixture. Sift flour, 2 cups at a time, and add to yeast/milk mixture.
Knead dough on floured board until dough forms a ball. Cut 3 loaves and press into 3 bread pans or 3 pie pans.
Let dough rise again until double (1 to 2 hours). Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes on center rack of oven.
Brush melted butter on top of bread and sprinkle top with sugar.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: You will need a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: chicken 'n broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed.
Place rice in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Layer cooked chicken (removed from bone) and cooked broccoli.
Mix 2 soups and broth together.
Pour over broccoli. Layer cheese slices on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Add onion rings and bake another 5 minutes.
Do not cover while baking.

title: fudge
directions: Cut up Hershey bar into small pieces.
Mix Hershey bar, chocolate chips, and marshmallow creme together and set aside. Mix sugar, milk, and butter.
Bring to boil and boil for two minutes.
Pour sugar mixture over chocolate mixture and stir until all chocolate is melted.
Add chopped nuts if desired.

title: chicken casserole(serves 8 to 12)
directions: Grease 7 x 11-inch flat casserole.
Spread 1/2 prepared stuffing mix in casserole.
Cover with chicken chunks.
Mix together celery, onion, mayo and lemon pepper; spoon over chicken. Cover with water chestnut slices.
Cover with remainder of stuffing mix.
Beat eggs with fork; add milk.
Pour over casserole.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, spoon the undiluted mushroom soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spread with grated Cheddar cheese and return to oven 15 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: beef jerky
directions: Remove all fat from roast and place in freezer until semi-frozen.
Slice roast into thin strips, approximately 3/8 to 1/4-inch.
Mix remaining ingredients to make marinade for beef. Marinate the beef slices in marinade for at least eight hours or overnight in a glass container in the refrigerator.
Be sure container has cover.
Stir beef several times to ensure all slices are saturated while marinating.
Drain in colander and place beef slices on dehydrator trays.
Do not overlap and turn slices at least once while drying.
Dry at 145° for 6 to 9 hours.
It is ready when it bends like a green willow without breaking.
Long term storage should be in the refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash that has been cut into pieces until tender.
Drain well.
Mix ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole.
Cover with stuffing and bake until bubbly at 350°.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in long baking dish. Mix baking
mix,
paprika,
salt
and
pepper;
coat chicken. Place skin side down in dish.
(Can also use skinned chicken.) Bake
for 35
minutes.
Turn.
Bake about 15 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased tube pan.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch glass pan, dump pineapple, then cherries and last cake mix (dry).
With the cube of butter, slice and cover top of dry cake mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yellow bundt cake
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350° in tube pan.
While hot, pour glaze over cake.

title: chicken celebre
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in single layer in large baking pan Place tomatoes, mushrooms and bay leaves on top of chicken. Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: banana-nut loaf
directions: Stir thoroughly the first 4 ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and peeling; beat well. Combine bananas and milk; add to creamed mixture alternately with flour mixture, beating just until smooth after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: breakfast cereal for all seasons
directions: Purchase rolled oats, rye flakes and wheat flakes in bulk. Mix together and store in airtight container.

title: macaroni and ham casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine macaroni, meat, soup, milk and sour cream; mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Arrange broccoli on top.
Cover and bake 30 to 35 minutes. Uncover and top with cheese; bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple butter pork loin
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Season the pork tenderloins with seasoning salt, and place them in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish or small roasting pan. Pour apple juice over the pork, and cover the dish with a lid or aluminum foil.

title: huckleberry jam - lite
directions: Remove stems from huckleberries and crush.
Measure 5 cups crushed huckleberries.
Add water.
Measure sugar into dry bowl. Mix 1/4 cup sugar from measured sugar and mix with pectin in small bowl.
Stir sugar mixture into fruit.
Add margarine to reduce foaming.
Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining sugar.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Skim and pour into prepared jars and seal.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix and pour into a hot, oiled, 10-inch cast-iron skillet and bake at 350° for 1 hour (approximately).

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown vermicelli and rice in butter (noodles first).
Heat chicken broth, salt, bouillon and parsley in saucepan.
After rice browns, put in casserole dish and pour broth over and add mushrooms.
Bake for 20 minutes, covered, at 350°.
After baking, rest 15 minutes in oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs to creamed mixture and mix well.
Mash bananas and add to mixture.
Gradually add flour. Add raisins and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: no cook-coconut cooky or candy
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in large bowl.
Leave out cocoa if you prefer.
In another pan mix together the sugar, milk and oleo.
Bring this to a rolling boil, then add vanilla.
Take from fire and add to first mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
If not thick enough add more oatmeal.
Put in refrigerator for several hours to set.

title: tater tot bake
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic, if desired.
Place in a 1 1/2 or 2-quart pan.
Top with Tater Tots.
Mix milk and soup; pour over all.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.
Sure is good.

title: pork pie
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir once in a while.
Add potato (cooked and mashed).
Add cracker crumbs.
Put in a pie shell and cover with a top crust.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: frosting for sugar cookies
directions: Add powdered sugar to whipped egg white.
If too runny, add more powdered sugar.
If too thick, add a few drops of water.
Add desired food coloring.
Frost cookies.
Let stand to set up.
Store in airtight container.

title: nut vegetable loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop the popcorn and place in a large brown grocery bag. In a large glass bowl, combine brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt. Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir.
Microwave on High 2 more minutes. Add baking powder and stir.
Pour caramel mixture over corn. Fold down top of bag and shake vigorously.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake.
Microwave on High 45 seconds. Shake. Microwave on High 30 seconds.
Shake. Spread on cookie sheet and cool.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Stir well.
Place in covered container.
Will keep in refrigerator 6 weeks.
Use as needed. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes in well-greased muffin tin.

title: baked apple pudding
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift the next 7 ingredients and add.
Add apples and nuts. Bake 45 minutes at 350° in dripper.
Serve hot with Pudding Sauce.

title: swedish tea ring
directions: In mixing bowl, add oil and water. Add eggs 1 at a time; beat well after each egg. Mix in butter extract and vanilla. Beat 8 minutes. Pour 1/2 batter in 10-inch Bundt cake pan (greased and floured). Sprinkle filling over batter. Add rest of batter.

title: wine biscuits
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; brush top with egg.
Put in ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Pour in bowl the remaining ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Add flour mixture and blend.
Roll out on a floured board 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out in various shapes.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Coat a Dutch oven with cooking spray; add oil and place over medium-high heat.
Add onion, celery, red pepper and garlic.
Cook.
Add flour.
Stir and cook 1 minute.
Gradually stir in chicken broth, water, potatoes, carrots, white pepper, thyme and bay leaves.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir often.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cook 5 minutes or until seafood is done.
Makes 10 servings.
Freezes very well.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine blueberries, sugar, flour, salt and lemon juice.
Fill pastry-lined pan.
Dot with butter and add top crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; then at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and egg together. Add flour, baking soda, salt, bananas, vanilla flavoring (add quickly) and buttermilk. Put in greased loaf pan. Cook at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add cream and vanilla. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir in raisins, nuts and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
Makes a flat, crisp cookie.

title: jello rice dessert
directions: Cook rice, drain and cool.
Mix Jell-O and water together; cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into deep bowl and chill until firm.

title: irish bread(moist)
directions: Crumble flour and butter with fingers.
Add raisins and rest of dry ingredients.
Mix egg and milk in separate bowl and whisk together.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix together.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour in 9-inch pie pan.
When done, brush with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Combine ground beef and bacon over low heat until brown. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients (draining part of the liquid off beans).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or can be put in crock-pot for several hours.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and milk together well.
Make small balls and place in shallow pan.
Cover with soup and water.
Bake in slow oven at 300° to 325° for 2 hours.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until soft; cut into chunks. Mix with onion, mayo and Velveeta cheese. Grease 9 x 12 dish. Add potato mixture. Top with sliced green olives and crumbled bacon. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Microwave butter and cocoa in a 2 1/2-quart glass casserole on High 2 minutes.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour batter into a 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Microwave on High 10 to 14 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn after 5 minutes.
Leave cake in pan.
Spread mini-marshmallows over warm cake.
Top with icing.

title: blueberry delight
directions: For the first layer, melt margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Spread evenly in dish and chill for an hour in the refrigerator.
Mix cream cheese, milk, and confectioners sugar.
Spread evenly over first layer.
Sprinkle chopped nuts evenly over cream cheese layer.
Allow 1 hour to chill in refrigerator.
Spread blueberry filling over nuts and chill for approximately 1 hour.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and mix in Jell-O.
Cool.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: coconut frosting
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water together to soft ball stage.
Pour gradually over beaten egg whites.
Beat constantly until mixture holds a peak.
Spread on cake; sprinkle with coconut.

title: pistachio almond cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove and complete cooling on a rack.
Sift powdered sugar on top.

title: teresa's meat loaf
directions: Combine oatmeal or cracker crumbs and eggs together.
Add tomato paste and remaining ingredients.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Reserve a small amount to sprinkle on top.
Pat crust in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and brown lightly in oven.
Cool.

title: doctor's punch
directions: Frozen juice may be used in place of canned.
Follow directions on cans.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix together and set aside.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heavily grease a 17 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Put 1/3 cup cooking oil in frying pan. Turn on medium.
Take chicken; flour it, put it in ice water and flour it again.
Fry it until golden brown.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, salt and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook, without stirring until 236° on candy thermometer or is a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and let stand until lukewarm (110°).
Add vanilla and pecans and beat with spoon until mixture begins to thicken and loses its gloss.
Drop from tablespoon onto wax paper.
Let stand until firm.
Store in airtight container.

title: sausage enchiladas
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet, drain. Pour over cream cheese in bowl. Mix until cream cheese is blended. Add rotel tomatoes and mix well. Spread tortillas with a thin layer of refried beans. Place 1/4 cup meat mixture in center with a pinch of cheese and roll up. Place in greased casserole dish. Top with cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in a greased casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cinnamon, ginger, salt, eggs and nutmeg. Add rich milk or evaporated milk.
Lastly, add pumpkin.
Pour into a pastry shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: hazelnut, pear and apricot pie
directions: Prepare a pastry for a single 9-inch pie.
Place the hazelnuts in a 8 or 9-inch wide pan.
Bake in a 350° oven until nuts are lightly browned under the skins (15 to 20 minutes).
Pour into a towel, rub lightly with towel to remove as much of the brown skins as possible.
Lift the nuts from the towel; discard the skins.

title: 6 layer casserole
directions: Put ground beef in skillet and cook until almost brown.
Add all the rest in layers and cook in oven until done.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans well at least 1 hour.
Heat vinegar and sugar until melted, then cool.
Add to beans, bell pepper, onion and pimiento. After vinegar and sugar has cooled, add salad oil and pour over vegetables.
Let it sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: ann's pasta salad
directions: Make Italian dressing with red wine vinegar.
Salad seasoning can also be McCormick, but Gordons is less expensive, or Salad Elegance from Penzey's.
Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: deer cube steak by joey
directions: Soak deer meat in cold water until all blood is drained.
Pat dry.
Sprinkle with Nature's Seasons and soak in buttermilk. Cover with flour.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Fry Granddaddy is perfect for cooking this dish.

title: gingerbread
directions: Pour molasses and hot water into big mixing bowl.
Add shortening, sugar and beaten egg to molasses mixture.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients, a little at a time, mixing well.
Bake in greased pans, 9 x 11-inches or 2 round pans at 375° until done, usually 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix margarine, chicken broth and Pepperidge Farm dressing all together.
Put half in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Next combine sour cream and chicken soup and pour over chicken.
Last put the rest of the dressing over that and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Spread 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Open out rolls and spread in pan.
Pinch perforated edges together.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread on rolls.
May need to microwave cream cheese 30 seconds or so.
Take second can of rolls and put over cream cheese mixture.	Pinch edges together.
Brush top with egg white.	Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cut into squares when cool.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix and add sliced cucumbers.

title: cheese topped potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
Cut diagonally with skin on in 1 1/2 inch slices.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt; brush with butter.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove from oven and top with cheese slices.
Return to oven about 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: piquant sauce for meat loaf
directions: Combine and put on top of meat loaf before baking.
This may also be put on top of the meat loaf when it is partly baked.

title: fruity chicken pita
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard and cinnamon.
Mix and chill.
Fill each pocket with 1/2 cup.

title: penuce fudge
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Add the butter.
Add either pecans or coconut or both.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: just for kids: peanut butter and honey sandwich
directions: Take a piece of bread and spread peanut butter on it.
Pour honey on the peanut butter and put the next piece of bread on it. Warm it up in the microwave for 30 seconds and enjoy.

title: egg and sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage in pan, drain.
Mix eggs, half and half, salt, and pepper together.
Layer in glass dish bread, then sausage, and then cheese.	Pour egg mixture over all.
Stand covered in refrigerator overnight.
Cook 45 minutes. Remove, let stand for 5 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Combine dry ingredients with butter and cheese.
Form into balls and freeze.
When ready to serve, take as many as needed from the freezer.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Great for ready to eat snacks!

title: asparagus bites
directions: Mix cream cheese with Blue cheese and add egg.
Count number of asparagus spears in can and then count out the same number of slices of bread.
Trim crusts from bread and roll slices as thin as possible.
Spread each slice of bread with cheese and egg mixture.
Place asparagus spears on each bread slice and roll up. Cut each rolled slice into thirds.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage until crumbly; drain.
Add onion and celery. Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add soup, water and rice; mix well. Pour into 8-inch casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sparkling sea breeze punch
directions: In 2-quart pitcher, combine cranberry juice, grapefruit juice, vodka, lime juice and sugar. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add wine. Stir briefly. Garnish with lime slices. Makes 16 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: chocolate jumbles
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on generously floured surface.
Cut with round cookie cutter with hole in center.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool 2 minutes and remove from cookie sheet.
Frost with Vanilla Glaze.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Put caramels and milk in top of double boiler (or use microwave).
Let melt and then set aside.
Dissolve gelatine in the water.
Whip cream and add to gelatine.
Fold into caramel mixture. Pour into graham cracker pie crust and trim with pecans.

title: ground turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or 1 hour.

title: mother's chocolate pie
directions: In a saucepan, cook the first 5 ingredients. Add the egg yolks and cook for a few minutes more. Add margarine and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell. Prepare meringue using the egg whites and sugar. Brown lightly under broiler.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creamed chicken or turkey on egg bread
directions: Brown celery and onion in butter until tender.
Add flour, then chicken stock.
Add cream and do not let come to boil.
Add chopped chicken, pimiento and peas and serve over Egg Bread.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally with wooden spoon.
Keep in sealed container.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all together and sprinkle over toast.
Sprinkle with 4 teaspoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: scrumptious salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add mashed cheese and marshmallows while hot.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Then stir in pineapple and whipped cream. Pour in 9 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: cake for diabetics
directions: Cook raisins with small amount of water until all liquid is gone.
Blend or mash up.
Combine all ingredients and bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until tester comes out clean.

title: biscuit rolls
directions: Combine and blend ingredients.
Mix well.
Fill ungreased small muffin tins to the top with batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut and pimentos.
Save juice from pimentos.
Mix ingredients with juice from pimentos.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Stir well before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with melted margarine.
Cover bottom of baking dish with layer of stuffing, chicken, soup and broth, then repeat, ending with stuffing.
Cook 45 minutes in 350° oven or until bubbly hot and slightly brown.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together and spread on cake layers.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottoms of 3 (9-inch) round cake pans with wax paper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute
onions
in butter.
Add flour and mix well.
Add milk, mushrooms and mushroom soup.
Stir until hot.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Put rice in bottom of greased casserole dish,
then the chicken.
Pour prepared sauce over this. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: pat's large salad
directions: Layer salad in large bowl in order of recipe.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.

title: ground beef-vegetable soup
directions: In Dutch oven or deep skillet, brown ground beef; drain excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 20 to 25 minutes or until veggies are tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: delicious bars
directions: Drain pears; reserve 1/2 of the liquid; dice and set aside. In large mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, vanilla and reserved pear syrup; mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; stir into butter mixture.
Add chocolate chips and diced pears.
Turn into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into bars while still warm.

title: meat loaf
directions: In medium mixing bowl, beat egg.
Add onion soup mix, bread crumbs and milk.
Mix together, let stand 5 minutes.
With a fork, mix in beef.
Mix together and shape into loaf.
Put in shallow pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 40 minutes.
Mix mustard and ketchup together in separate bowl.
Brush on 2 to 3 times while baking.
After 40 minutes, put Mozzarella cheese slices on top and return to oven.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple-oatmeal crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spread the sliced apples over the bottom of a greased 8 x 8 x 2 inch baking dish. In a mixing bowl, combine the brown and granulated sugars, flour and oats (may add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg), then stir in the melted butter. Spread mixture over the apples. Pour the water evenly over the top. Bake, uncovered, about 30 minutes until the apples are tender. Serve warm or at room temperature with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Melt butter and Cheez Whiz; mix with other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage.
Cube chicken; set aside.
Fry onion in oil. Add flour; cook until flour is brown.
Add water and all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Lower heat; cover.
Raise lid occasionally to stir, but not too often.
Cook until rice is tender, about 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sugar and flour and pat in bottom.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Whip cream cheese until soft; add Cool Whip and layer over crust.
Spoon apple filling on cream cheese.
Mix sour cream with cinnamon.
Spread evenly over filling.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding water and sour cream last.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, making halves of cookie.
After baked, take off pan; cool on wax paper. Continue baking until all dough is used.
Match 2 halves, putting icing between.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in casserole dish; stir well.
Add topping.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift first four ingredients together.
Set aside.
Cream shortening with electric mixer.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
On low speed, add flour mixture and mashed bananas alternately.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured bread tin.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minuets.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: tuna roll
directions: Mix tuna
and
cheese
until smooth; add other ingredients. Wrap in Saran Wrap and put in fridge for several hours. Serve with your favorite crackers or toast rounds.

title: pretty fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and cherries; throw away.
Drain juice from peaches and pineapple; save.
Prepare all fruits, except bananas.
Set aside.
Cook the pudding mix in 1 3/4 cups peach and pineapple juice until thick.
Let cool completely.
Cut bananas in 1/2-inch chunks; fold pudding over all the fruit mixture.

title: berry cake
directions: Cream shortening, salt and sugar together.
Beat eggs; add to shortening mixture.
Add milk, flour and baking powder.
Mix together well.
Add berries; stir gently.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan and add batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute ground beef and sausage, garlic and oregano until done. Add spaghetti sauce and simmer while noodles cook.
Line 8 x 13-inch baking dish with noodles, add a layer of spinach and layer of noodles.
Pour meat and sauce over noodles.
Sprinkle on Feta cheese, add remaining noodles and top with Mozzarella.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: baked cabbage casserole
directions: Layer shredded cabbage, sausage and onion soup mix.
Add water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the last 3 and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top and pour margarine over mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Cover the sliced cucumbers with the lime and 2 gallons of water.
Soak 24 hours; drain and rinse.
Cover with cold water; soak 3 hours.
Drain and cover with the vinegar.
Use 4 pounds sugar and 2 tablespoons salt and soak overnight.
Add the celery salt, cloves and pickling spice.
Boil for 25 minutes; seal in hot jars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add soup, onion, cheese, eggs and mayonnaise.
Saute dressing in a small amount of butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until hot and starts to bubble.

title: campbelled eggs
directions: In medium bowl, stir soup until smooth. Gradually beat in eggs and pepper.
In 10-inch skillet over low heat, melt margarine. Pour in egg mixture.
As eggs begin to set, stir lightly so uncooked egg mixture flows to bottom.
Cook until set, but still very moist.
If desired, garnish with parsley.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix ingredients in electric freezer can.
Freeze.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, 1 1/4 cups sugar, salt, eggs, 1/3 stick margarine, sweet milk, 1/2 cup flour and vanilla.
Pour in a buttered dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour, nuts and 1/3 stick margarine and sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: poulet la liberte
directions: Cook broccoli al dente.
Layer on bottom of baking pan. Prepare chicken; pat dry and season with salt and pepper.
Layer chicken over broccoli, pushing broccoli completely under chicken. With a wire whip, mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder until creamy smooth.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle generously with bread crumbs, grated cheese and paprika.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with fettucine or rice pilaf.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs until very light. Add sugar and continue beating until well mixed. Add pineapple, mace and lemon juice. Mix with a spoon until well blended.
Pour into a greased casserole and cover top with bread cubes that have been coated with melted butter. Bake 1/2 hour in moderate oven at 350°.
Use as vegetable with ham, pork or chicken.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Generously butter a 12-inch plate.
Combine the sugar, milk and salt in a small saucepan.
Heat to soft ball stage (240° on thermometer); turn off the heat.
Stir in the vanilla, butter and peanut butter.
Mix well and pour onto buttered plate.
Let cool, then cut into squares.
Makes about 2 dozen pieces.

title: barbecued frankfurters
directions: Place frankfurters in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Saute onion in butter in a saucepan until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over frankfurters. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake in a loaf pan or 2 round pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet brie with pastry
directions: Lay crescent rolls on flat surface.
Pinch dotted lines together, then use floured rolling pin to make 1 large sheet of pastry dough.
Place brie in the middle of the dough.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of brown sugar and pecans.
Scoop dough around brie and pinch together at the top.
Sprinkle remaining brown sugar and pecans over the dough.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and dry ingredients. Knead if necessary to get all of flour in.
Make 3 or 4 rolls and chill.
Slice and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
One half cup nuts may be added.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar thoroughly, then add flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Boil butter and water together, then pour over the dough and mix well.
Mix in chopped almonds.
The cake is baked in a special grooved pan which is about 4 inches across and 11 inches long and resembles a tube which has been cut lengthwise.
Grease and flour pan and pour batter in; bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
If you wish, just before serving sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil eggs.
Boil potatoes whole until done.
Cut into chunks. Place potatoes in a bowl.
Add chopped eggs, pickles and onions. Mix in mustard and mayonnaise.
Add salt and pickle juice.
Mix together well.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies(with cream filling)
directions: Cream butter and both sugars until white and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and soda together; add to mixture.
Stir in oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mouth watering caramel corn
directions: Set popped corn aside.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add sugar, vanilla and syrup.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; stir occasionally.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Fry ground beef.
Add onions.
Cook until lightly brown.
Add soups.
Break up tortillas in bottom of a casserole, then layer of meat mixture and cheese (grated).
Alternate layers until all mixture is used.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Uncover last 20 minutes.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Mix the rest in usual manner. Bake in oblong pan in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: molasses bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Add all ingredients.
Beat until smooth. Pour mixture in greased pan.
Cook until golden brown.

title: cheezy chex snack
directions: Melt butter on low heat in large skillet.
Spread out cheese. Stir gently, as it melts and is bubbly.
With cheese spread over bottom of pan, pour on cereal.
Turn to coat with cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: gaelic chops(ireland)
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
In a 10-inch skillet, brown chops in hot butter on both sides.
Sprinkle chops lightly with some salt and pepper.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, adding a little more butter, if necessary.
Remove chops to a heated serving platter; keep warm.
Spoon excess fat from pan juices.
Stir in whipping cream and whiskey.
Heat gently until hot, stirring up the brown bits in skillet.
Do not boil. Immediately pour the cream sauce over chops.
Garnish with parsley or watercress.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in casserole dish.
Cover with sauce made from whole cranberries, jellied cranberries, Lipton soup mix and French dressing.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with any rice.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Blend together sugar, butter, egg yolks, milk and flour.
Add juice and rind of 1 lemon.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites; pour into crust and bake in slow oven.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted ingredients and mix well.
Add oats, cornflakes and coconut and mix all together.
Cookies may be formed into balls or dropped by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.	Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix the gingersnaps with melted butter.
Pat into a 9-inch pie pan and bake for 10 minutes at 300°.
While the crust is baking, mix together the whipped topping, pudding and pineapple.
Pour into the cooled crust and top with almonds and coconut.
Wrap in your love and deliver with a blessing card.
The Lord bless you and keep you.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Put dry ingredients in bowl.
Cut shortening through it.
Mix egg with milk; pour into flour mixture and beat smooth.
Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients, then add Karo, pecans and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: souper easy cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in 3-quart saucepan.
Heat over medium heat until hot.

title: white house dressing
directions: Place all in blender, except oil. Blend 10 seconds. Add oil. Blend 10 seconds. Serve on lettuce greens.

title: ground beef soup
directions: Fry ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Put water in 2-quart pan and mix in beef, tomato sauce and chili beans.
Cook over medium heat about 30 minutes.

title: crispy corn dogs
directions: You will also need 12 skewers.

title: quick and easy sour beets
directions: Combine margarine, vinegar and sugar in 1-quart saucepan over medium heat. Bring to boil. Add beets and stir. Heat thoroughly. Season to taste.

title: rhubarb custard cake
directions: Put rhubarb on the bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle sugar over rhubarb.
Mix cake mix together and pour over rhubarb. Pour whipping cream over undone cake mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Store in refrigerator after cool.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat the egg into milk. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into hot oil.

title: lemon bar deluxe
directions: Sift flour and powdered sugar; cut in margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Beat eggs, granulated sugar and lemon juice.
Sift flour and baking powder; add to egg mixture.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional powdered sugar.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: hamburger-macaroni casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and drain off all fat.
Cook macaroni in water with the 1 tablespoon of butter until tender. Drain.

title: new england dinner au gratin
directions: Place cabbage, potatoes, carrots and leeks in 4-quart Dutch oven.
Sprinkle spices over vegetables and mix well.
Add water.

title: dixie lily basic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until mixed; add enough milk to make soft dough.
Stir with a fork only until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead just until smooth.

title: tidewater stew
directions: In kettle or Dutch oven, saute butter, onion, celery, green pepper and mushrooms.
Add oysters, milk and potatoes.
Bring to simmer.
When oysters have curled in the stew, add crumbled bacon and sprinkle on oregano.
Serve hot with generous serving of buttered cornbread.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cook onion in minimum water for 7 minutes.
Add milk, lobster or fish and potatoes.
Boil gently until potatoes are soft, about 15 minutes.
Add soup, cream, butter, m.s.g. and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until heated through.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all together and cook to soft boil stage, stirring constantly.
Put pan in cold water in sink and stir constantly until pan is cool to touch of hand (just until you can hold your hand on it).
Beat and spread.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Saute onion in margarine, set aside.
Cook spaghetti.
Put half of spaghetti in a casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 of the cheese.
Add remainder of spaghetti.
Top with remaining cheese. Pour tomato juice over top.
Top with onion and margarine.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter to consistency of mayonnaise.
Add sugar gradually, while still continuing to cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Place
flour,
salt
and pepper in plastic food storage bag. Dredge beef
cubes in flour mixture.
In large saucepot, brown beef and carrots in oil in batches for 6 to 8 minutes or until browned.
Remove to bowl.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in tube pan and cook at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: norwegian pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and eggs.
Mix well.
Add baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pie plates or pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lobster thermidor
directions: Prepare cream sauce using egg shade for coloring.
Combine with all the above ingredients, except cheese, paprika, sherry wine and bread crumbs.
Fill the lobster shells with this mixture; sprinkle with mixture of cheese and bread crumbs.
Top with paprika for color.
Moisten tops with sherry wine.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bacon water chestnuts
directions: You will need wooden toothpicks.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in one large bowl.
Mix last 3 ingredients in another large bowl with any cabbage left (shredded). Take cabbage and put a utility fork in core and dip in large hot kettle of water.
While in water, cut leaves from top off cabbage. Put undamaged leaves on side for stuffing.
Shred or tear other leaves into small pieces to use in between layers.
Stuff cabbage with ingredients in first bowl.
Fold sides and bottom up and roll.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and rinse macaroni.
Cut fresh vegetables into small pieces.
Add to macaroni.
Mix with dressing.
Chill.
Serve cold.

title: tuna rice casserole
directions: In a saucepan, combine soup, water, onion, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour half of the soup mixture in dish.
Sprinkle uncooked rice on top of soup mixture.
Spoon peas and tuna on as next layers and sprinkle cheese next (save small amount of cheese to sprinkle on top).
Pour remaining hot soup mixture on and sprinkle remaining cheese.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
After the first 10 minutes of baking, make cuts into casserole to mix cheese around better.
Continue to bake.
Cool slightly and serve. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: In a blender or food processor, puree all the ingredients until smooth (about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes).

title: waldorf salad
directions: Peel and chop apples into bite-size pieces.
Pour lemon juice over apples to keep them fresh and from turning brown.
Add mayonnaise, celery and pecans.
Mix together thoroughly.
Wrap with Saran Wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: moistest cake ever
directions: Mix and pour into desired pan (12-Cup Bundt).
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Cut apple into 10 pieces.
Pat out biscuit and put an apple piece in it and wrap it up.
Place them in a long pan, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bring Sprite, sugar and butter to a boil. Pour over dumplings, sprinkle again with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: In a large glass bowl crumble ground beef and microwave on High for
to
4	minutes
or until brown, stirring once. Drain fat; stir
in
sauce, water and garlic.
In another bowl combine Ricotta, eggs
and	pepper.
In
a	3 quart dish spoon sauce to lightly
cover
bottom
of	dish.
Alternately layer noodles, egg mixture,
Mozzarella
and
sauce.
(Do
not cook noodles.) Microwave
on
High
covered
8 minutes;
turn once, then microwave at Medium-low, covered, for 30 to 35 minutes or until noodles
are
tender.
Top with Parmesan cheese and let stand 15 minutes, covered.

title: margie's corn chow
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand 5 minutes.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Place in cans and seal.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix soda with flour.
Combine margarine, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually mix in flour and soda.
Stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook sausage over low heat.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic. Saute until tender. Add red beans, tomatoes and seasonings. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Great served with corn bread.

title: apricot or peach preserves
directions: Stir well.
Cook about 40 minutes.
It will thicken after it stands.

title: sunny day punch
directions: Combine Punch and juices. Add ginger ale just before serving. Serve over ice.
Makes 10 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add cooking oil, eggs, apples and nuts.
Dough will be very stiff.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips over top. Press dough firmly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
If using self-rising flour, omit salt, soda and baking powder.

title: hot clam spread
directions: Combine all the above into the casserole you will be cooking and serving in.
Can make this the day before and reheat when serving; the flavor is better.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1/2 hour, covered with foil. Remove foil and brown 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done, then shred (save broth).
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Place one pie crust into a deep dish pan.
Pour mixture into the crust.
Top with second crust, tucking it under the edge of the bottom one; crimp.
Cut three small slits in top of crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into twenty 1-inch balls.
Cook over medium heat, turning occasionally, until brown, about 20 minutes. Or cook in ungreased oblong pan, 9 x 13-inch, at 400° until light brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk; bring to a full boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, then Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan; cool and cut.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain pears and arrange in dish.
Heat pear juice to boiling; add jello and stir until dissolved.
Pour mixture over Philadelphia cream cheese in large mixing bowl and whip until smooth with electric mixer.
Add Cool Whip and mix until blended. Pour over pears and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Cut into squares and top each square with a cherry.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels,
oleo
and
tablespoons sugar. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.	Cool.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Roll in ball size of walnut, flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tart punch
directions: Fill the punch bowl halfway with ice.
Add 7-Up and lemonade. Stir.
Serves 30 to 40.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Heat soup. Pour over jello. Let cool after mixing. Add other ingredients. Let jell. Good with ham, pork roast or spicy meats.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Whip well until all peaches are smooth.
Pour in ungreased 10 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven.
Let cake cool.

title: ground round soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until carrots are tender.
Then add 1 cup baby pastina or soup mac noodles and cook until done.

title: almond green beans
directions: Melt oleo and shaved almonds.
Stir a little.
Add flour and stir well.
Add milk, soup and cheese.
Let cheese melt.
Pour this over green beans in baking dish.
Top with 1 cup buttered bread crumbs (optional).
Bake in 400° oven about 15 or 20 minutes until hot throughout.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Mix half the sauce mixture with spaghetti and place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: cranberry crisp coffee cake
directions: Mix crushed cereal with butter or oleo; set aside.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat 1/4 cup butter or oleo, sugar and egg until smooth.
Spread cake batter in 9-inch pan.
Top with cranberry sauce.
Sprinkle with cereal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter (use a large pan).
Mince potatoes in small cubes and add to the onion and barely cover with water.
Cook until mushy.
Add soup to cooked potatoes; add cubed cheese.
When cheese melts, add milk and turn to simmer.

title: crusty ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Pour off grease.
Add chili powder, garlic and tomato sauce.
Spread in 12 x 8 1/2-inch dish.
Add cheese, then beans over cheese.
Mix cornbread mix according to package directions.
Spoon over beans.
Cook at 375° until golden brown.

title: lima beans and tomatoes
directions: Cook lima beans in small amount of water until tender.
Drain excess water.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Add to tomatoes (may cut into smaller pieces).
Cook cornstarch and tomatoes until juice is thick.
Add cooked lima beans and seasoning and heat.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Drain the crushed pineapple and save the juice. Add the boiling water to lemon Jello, stirring until dissolved. Add 7-UP and remaining ingredients in order listed. Chill until firm.

title: spring fruitcake
directions: Make cake as directed, adding oranges with juice.
Bake and let cool.
Drain pineapple.
Make pudding using 1 cup milk only. Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix and pour on cake.

title: green beans
directions: Wash green beans; trim ends and remove strings.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place beans and sliced red chile pepper in a 2-quart baking dish.
Add water; cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Microwave at High for 12 to 14 minutes, or until beans are tender, stirring twice.
Let stand, covered, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: indonesian steak
directions: Saute steak in 1/2 of the oil.
Brown meat well.
Remove from pan.
Put remaining oil in pan, lower heat and saute onions and garlic.
Put steak back in pan.
Add sugar, water and soy sauce. Lower heat to simmer, cover tightly and cook 1 hour.
Add mushrooms after about 45 minutes.

title: jiffy cobbler
directions: *Use your choice of fruit: apples, peaches or pineapple (in heavy syrup).

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish (use margarine or cooking spray).
Drizzle 1/4 to 1/2 cup melted butter or margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: In 1-quart casserole, blend together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in milk, mixing well.
Microwave at High 5 to 7 minutes, stir every 3 minutes until mixture is smooth, thickened and clear.
Stir a small amount of hot pudding quickly into egg, returning egg mixture to hot pudding, mixing well. Microwave at medium-high 1 to 3 minutes, stirring after 1 minute until smooth and thickened.
Add butter and vanilla, stir until butter is melted.
Add the already cooked rice and pour into serving dishes.
Let set for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding by directions, then add Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well.
Layer vanilla wafers or graham crackers, bananas and pudding.
Real easy and so good.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Bring water, salt, sugar and shortening to a boil and boil for 1 minute; cool until warm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water and add to water mixture.
Beat at high speed in mixing bowl with eggs and 4 cups of flour for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add rest of flour (3 cups) by hand.
Place in covered, buttered bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Shape into desired rolls.
Bake at 400°.

title: delicious fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to the soft ball stage.
Immediately remove from heat; add margarine, chips, marshmallows, nuts and vanilla.
Mix and stir well until all chips and marshmallows are melted.
Pour into a flat pan (cookie sheet).
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Remove and cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds of fudge.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Into a heavy saucepan, put flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Set aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend all together.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: creamy salsa dip
directions: Cream together with mixer.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions; keep warm.

title: three layer jello
directions: Drain fruit cocktail into measuring cup.
Put fruit in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix lime jello with 2 cups hot water and 1 cup cold water.
Pour over fruit and jell.
Mix lemon jello with 1 cup juice from fruit, 2 cups hot water and cream cheese.
Use mixer.
Pour over first layer; jell.
Mix cherry jello with 1 cup hot water and 2 cups cold water and pour over top.
When almost jelled, sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a 1-cup measure, mix the juice and grated rind from the orange.
Add the shortening and enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients.
Add the egg and cranberries and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and let stand for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
This recipe is easily doubled.

title: dill dip(vegetable dip)
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill several hours to blend flavors.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
To serve, mix 2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water or 3 teaspoons per mug of boiling water.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, orange juice and eggs well.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) cake pans and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Dissolve the confectioners sugar in the lime juice and spoon over the hot cake layers.
Mix butter, cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla well.
Spread over cake layers.

title: imelda's lumpia recipe
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cut onion and carrots into cubes and place in a food processor.
Dice, slice or cut to your liking. Avoid letting your mix get too watery.
Mix this into the ground beef with the garlic powder, black pepper and salt.

title: quick treats
directions: Break
graham
cracker
in half.
Place on small plate. Put Hershey bar on top of cracker.
Add marshmallow;
top with remaining
half
of graham cracker.
Microwave for 10 seconds. Remove from microwave carefully.

title: chess cake squares
directions: First bowl, mix cake mix, egg and margarine.
Press out in sheet cake pan.

title: rhubarb-strawberry upside-down cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with rhubarb.
Sprinkle sugar and jello over rhubarb; pour 1 cup water over mixture and set aside. Mix cake mix, 2/3 cup water, butter and eggs together.
Pour over rhubarb mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pink apple
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving syrup.
Pour boiling water over gelatin in bowl, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Add enough cold water to reserved syrup to measure 1 cup; stir until dissolved gelatin.
Chill until almost set.
In chilled bowl, beat cream until stiff.
(If using dessert topping mix, prepare as directed on package.)
Beat gelatin until foamy.
Fold gelatin and strawberries into whipped cream.
Pour into 1-quart mold or into individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold; if desired, serve with sweetened whipped cream or Creamy Stirred Custard and garnish with strawberries or other fruits.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add well beaten egg yolks, lemon rind, juice, melted butter and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn into a pastry-lined pan and bake at 450° about 5 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake about 45 minutes longer or until firm.
Cool before serving.

title: cabbage stew
directions: In a saucepan, fry the bacon and onion until the bacon is crisp.
Remove the bacon, chop and set side.
Add tomatoes, bouillon, sugar and pepper or salsa.
As the tomato mixture comes to a boil, chop the cabbage.
Mix it in and simmer 20 minutes. Stir in flour and bring to a boil.
Place in a serving bowl and garnish with chopped bacon.
Serves 10.

title: fudgey brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in a mixing bowl. Blend in 1/3 cup oil and boiling water. Stir until mixture thickens, then stir in sugar, eggs and remaining oil. Mix until smooth and creamy. Now add your flour, vanilla and salt. Blend completely. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs and bananas; beat well.
Add in order given:
soda, baking powder, salt, flour, milk, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple pie
directions: Pour apple pie filling in unbaked pie shell.
Spread the cake mix over the pie filling.
Then dot the 1/2 stick oleo over the cake mix.
Put in oven and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: amaretto pears
directions: Peel the pears and core them.
Be careful not to cut all the way to the bottom.
Fill it with sugar and pour Amaretto over the sugar.
Steam them for 45 minutes or until they are soft.
Cool a little and pour whipped cream over them.

title: zesty hot dog relish
directions: In medium-size bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, spices and add to apples.
Fill 9-inch pastry lined pan and hot margarine.
Adjust top crust and bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: grandma's tuna casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles until tender; drain.
Put in deep baking dish. Add drained tuna, cream of mushroom soup and peas or broccoli (your choice).
Mix very well.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1/2 quart strawberries;
mix with water, sugar and cornstarch.
Boil until thick and clear.
Put whole berries in baked pie crust.
Pour sauce over berries.
Chill until firm. Serves 8.

title: tomato and basil pasta with baked meatballs
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; let sit at room temperature at least one hour.
Then add the tomato mixture to cooked and drained pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Prepare baked meatballs and top pasta with them.
Serve with garlic bread and a tossed salad.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set for 1 hour at least.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in a 2-quart casserole baking dish, covered with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and brown.
Good hot or cold.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Mix other ingredients in a pan.
Add bacon with grease.
Cook at medium heat until reasonably thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over your choice of salad greens and mix well.
You may let vegetables cook a few minutes in a pan with dressing on them or pour over the fresh vegetables.

title: southwest stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta shells according to package directions and set aside. Combine pumpkin and next 4 ingredients; stuff each shell with mixture.
Spread 1 cup picante sauce into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place filled shells on sauce. Top with remaining sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle with Monterey Jack cheese and parsley.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni (until just tender).
Combine macaroni with drained tuna (sprinkle on a little lemon juice), mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Add the rest and stir until well mixed.
Turn into 9 x 5-inch loaf pans, greased on bottom only. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool before serving.
Looks good at Christmastime.
Good luck.

title: cowboy oatmeal cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Mix oil, margarine and sugar well.
Add eggs and rest of the ingredients a little at a time, then add the oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix good.
Cook at 350° until it starts to bubble.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream margarine and eggs. Add sugar; alternate milk and crackers. Add other ingredients. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut for 3 minutes on high speed.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup coconut. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Garnish with rest of coconut.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Put milk, chocolate chips, marshmallows and salt into heavy, 1-quart pan.
Stir over medium heat until chocolate chips and marshmallows melt and mixture thickens.
Cool to room temperature.

title: chicken rice entree
directions: Place rice in bottom of baking dish.
Cover with diced chicken.
Combine mushroom soup, water and 1 envelope onion soup mix; blend well and pour over rice.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 envelope of onion soup mix over casserole.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: granola
directions: Melt honey and butter on low heat.
Add cinnamon.
In huge mixing bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Pour honey-butter over dry mixture and mix thoroughly.
Spread in shallow pans and bake overnight at 175°.
Granola is also great for using residue heat after baking something else.
(It's far easier to fix than it may first appear.)

title: crunchy fudge crispies
directions: In a large saucepan over low heat, melt butter and marshmallows.
Remove from heat; add chips and vanilla, stirring until melted.
Stir in cereal.
Turn into lightly buttered 8 inch pan.
Chill.
Cut into bars.
Store covered at room temperature.

title: pound cake (delish)
directions: Cream butter; add powdered sugar and beat until smooth and creamy.
Add one egg and 1/2 cup flour at a time, beating each time; when eggs and flour are all added, add whiskey and blend well.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all together in a punch bowl and serve.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients well in a small bowl.
Combine Miracle Whip, honey and lemon juice.
Refrigerate all until serving time. In a large bowl, toss dressing over chicken-apples-celery-pecans. Place on lettuce leaves.
Serve with hot, crusty French bread.

title: fudge brownies for microwave only
directions: Place chocolate in small glass mixing bowl.
Heat in microwave 3 minutes, until chocolate is melted.
Add butter; heat 1 minute. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat 2 minutes.
Stir in flour and salt, just until well blended.
