Pour into an 8-inch square dish. Sprinkle chopped nuts over batter.
Cook in microwave oven 7 minutes, giving dish 1/2 turn after 3 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Put onions, green
pepper,
red
pepper
or carrots and pimento in a large mixing
bowl;
put 1 cup sugar over top and mix.
Bring vinegar, Wesson oil, 2 teaspoons sugar and salt to a boil.
Pour hot
mixture over cabbage mixture and mix.
Keep refrigerated overnight, then
ready to use.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: hot chicken 'n chip salad
directions: Combine ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Sprinkle cheese and chips on top.
Very good.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, or longer for larger or until heated through.

title: crock-pot steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Place in crock-pot.
Add soup mix, water and mushroom soup.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Excellent with mashed potatoes.

title: hot-milk sponge cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Heat milk and butter until butter melts.
Keep hot.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon-colored, about 3 minutes, on high speed mixer.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add sifted dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Stir just until blended.
Stir in hot milk mixture and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into greased pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar until quite thick; add the water, then the flour, salt and baking powder sifted together twice.
Line a shallow pan with greased paper (wax paper) or sprayed with Pam, pour in the batter evenly, and bake in a quick oven about 20 minutes.
Turn out on cloth or paper sprinkled with sugar, tear off the paper and spread with jam or jelly.
Roll up quickly.

title: mississippi salad
directions: Mix all together.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: swiss chicken with cherry tomatoes and zucchini
directions: To make low-fat, use one cup of chicken bouillon to cook onion, garlic and chicken instead of oil and butter.

title: st louis gooey butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/2 cup butter and 1 egg.
Beat well.
Press into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, remaining 2 eggs, remaining 1/2 cup butter and box of powdered sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cake.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: spicy bean and beef pie
directions: Put bottom crust in pie tin.
Cook beef and garlic.
Combine soup, 1 cup picante, cornstarch, parsley, paprika, salt and pepper; mix well.
Fold in beans, 1 1/4 cups cheese, 1/2 cup onions and beef mixture.
Top with remaining pastry.
Cut slits in top. Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Garnish with sour cream, olives, picante, cheese and onions.
Makes 8 servings.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Mix in chips and nuts.
Mix in flour.
Roll in small balls, place on a cookie sheet, then mash down with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple (including juice) and bananas.
Pour half the mixture into mold. Chill until firm. Spread sour cream over chilled mixture. Pour remaining mixture over sour cream.
Chill until firm.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix cornstarch into 1/2 cup milk.
Mix all ingredients well. Pour into unbaked pie crust; bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, crabmeat and 1 tablespoon horseradish (optional).
Line small round bowl with plastic wrap. Place mixture into bowl and press in until packed.
Cover and place in refrigerator until firm.
Remove from bowl and plastic wrap onto serving dish. Top with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix and cook all ingredients over medium-low heat until it forms
a
soft
ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and
beat until glossy.
Pour in buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: ham olive pinwheels
directions: Add enough mayonnaise to cream cheese so that it will spread easily.
Add olives.
Spread onto ham slices.
Roll.
Refrigerate overnight; slice.

title: pretzel salad(a dessert)
directions: Crust:
To crush pretzels, wrap about a cup at a time between wax paper and crush with a rolling pin.
Add melted margarine and 3 tablespoons of sugar to crushed pretzels.
Mix well and press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan or glass dish.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Take a layer of yellow cake and tear into pieces in bottom of large bowl.
Put 1 large package of instant vanilla pudding mix according to box; pour over cake.
Drain large can pineapple (crushed); pour over pudding.
Put cherry pie filling, cool Whip, then add pecans and coconut if desired.

title: chocolate-coconut drops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate in saucepan over low heat; remove from heat and stir in milk, coconut and walnuts.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Place in oven, turn off heat.
Leave in oven about 15 minutes or until candy has glazed appearance.
While warm, remove from baking sheet.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into paper cups in muffin pans. Freeze. Makes 24 to 30 frozen muffin salads.

title: christmas salad
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve lime gelatin in hot water.
Add crushed pineapple that has been drained.
Combine pineapple juice and enough water to make 1 cup.
Add and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan and chill.
Dissolve cherry gelatin in hot water. Immediately beat in the jellied cranberry sauce.
Chill slightly and spoon over top of lime layer when it is firm.
Soften cream cheese, stir in powdered sugar and add to topping that has been prepared, according to directions or to Cool Whip.
Beat this together real well.
Spread over top of red layer.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over top.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: crumb-coated chicken
directions: In small bowl, beat together eggs, butter and salt.
In shallow dish, place crumbs.
Coat chicken with crumbs, then egg mixture and crumbs again.
In a 2-quart oblong glass baking dish, arrange chicken with meatiest pieces to outside edges of dish. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High (10) for 16 to 19 minutes.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in balls.
Roll in white sugar.
Press down with glass to flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: overnight caramel french toast
directions: In small saucepan, combine syrup, butter and sugar.
Cook until sugar melts.
Pour over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay 6 slices of bread on top of this.
Mix eggs, milk, vanilla and salt in a bowl. Pour part over bread.
Add remaining bread and pour remaining egg mix evenly over top.
Cover pan and refrigerate overnight.

title: blueberry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve 2 packages raspberry gelatin in 3 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour in an 8 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Soften unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Dissolve gelatin and sugar in hot half and half.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat cream cheese in bowl until creamy.
Add half and half mixture, beating until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour over raspberry gelatin.
Chill until firm.

title: baked custard
directions: Mix all together.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Place dish in larger pan with about 2-inches of water. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers; remove stem ends, seeds and membranes.
Cook 5 minutes in boiling salted water; drain.
Brown beef and onion, stirring with fork.
Add remaining ingredients, except tomato sauce.
Fill peppers and place in deep baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over tops and around peppers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Coat chicken and fry in Crisco oil about 8 minutes per side on medium to high heat.
Turn often.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix by hand; cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix well; combine flour, soda and salt together.
Add buttermilk and banana and mix well.
Add vanilla; add flour mixture and nuts and mix well.
Bake 60 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, then add dried beef (cut into small chunks).
Mix together, then add remaining ingredients.
Can be rolled in chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: mulled cider mix
directions: Place brown sugar in a decorative tin or a small jar with resealable lid.
Tie spices and peel in cheesecloth and add to jar.
Seal tightly.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter, garlic salt and parsley to a soft cream.
Spread mixture on one slice of bread.
Add second slice and spread with mixture.
Cut into 4 squares.
Spread mixture on the sides of each square.
Place on cookie sheet.
Cover with foil; refrigerate until 20 minutes before serving.
Remove foil; bake until lightly browned.

title: cheese pie lunch
directions: Pour into blender cottage cheese, powdered milk, powdered sugar, vanilla and lemon.
Put Knox gelatine into cup; add cold water to blend it.
Add boiling water to gelatin.
Mix it well; pour it into blender.
Blend; add ice cubes, one at a time into blender.
Add pineapple or frozen strawberries.

title: date bars
directions: Mix together, bake and cover with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, then mix (sift) the flour together.
Add to first mixture. Add oats, chips and nuts last. Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until done.

title: the bog man's cranberry bread
directions: Mix in small bowl, first 5 ingredients.
Cream in large bowl, butter, sugar, egg, berries and cranberry juice.
Alternate mixing flour into fruits with milk.
Add nuts if desired.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 1/4 hours.

title: big cookies
directions: Grease 12-inch pizza pan.
Line with waxed paper.
Grease waxed paper.
Place all of cookie dough on paper.
Cover with another piece of waxed paper (ungreased).
Press or roll out cookie dough to completely cover pan evenly.
Remove top sheet of waxed paper.
Bake until set and slightly browned.
Remove from oven; cool completely.
Flip onto flat plate or pan.
Remove waxed paper from bottom of cookie.
Turn over and decorate if desired. Can be used in conjunction with any recipe making 3 dozen cookies.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Brown hamburger and onion. Spread in dish.
Pour soup over hamburger.
Cover with cheese slices.
Put Tater Tots over top.
Bake at 325° at least 1 1/4 hours.
Can be frozen before or after baking.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: butterscotch pecan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by rounded teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet. Cook at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Wash peppers and cut off the tops. Clean out the centers.
Cook for 2 minutes on High in a covered 2-quart casserole with the 1/4 cup water in the microwave.
Drain water and put peppers aside.

To lose most of the fat from the hamburger, place a plastic colander inside a microwaveproof pie plate or dinner plate and brown hamburger in the colander on High power for 2 minutes in the microwave.
The fat wil drop through the holes into the pie pan.
After 2 minutes, rearrange the meat with a fork to brown evenly.
Continue with 2 minutes of cooking until all the hamburger is browned.
Mix all the remaining ingredients in the 2-quart casserole dish.
Stuff some of the mixture and cook, covered, on High for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: devilishly deviled eggs
directions: Cool, peel and cut eggs in half lengthwise. Remove yolk and place in a small mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Spoon into eggs. Sprinkle with paprika. Serve.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs.
Beat egg yolks and water. Add to first mixture, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes in hot oven.

title: spinach cheese manicotti
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Place 1 cup spaghetti sauce in dish bottom.
Stir in water and set aside.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips over hot water (not boiling).
Add noodles and peanuts and put on wax paper by teaspoons.

title: chocolate mexicano
directions: Combine cocoa, brown sugar, water, cinnamon sticks, cloves and a pinch of salt in a pan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to low; simmer for about 5 minutes.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles, using package directions; drain.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, celery, onion, red and green peppers and salt in large mixing bowl.
Blend cream of mushroom soup and milk; heat through.
Add cheese; heat and stir until cheese melts. Add to noodle mixture carefully.
Mix and then put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
If desired, sprinkle with bread crumbs or slivered almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken breast in enough water to cover.
Add 1/2 onion, salt and dash of pepper; bring to a boil, then cook 20 to 25 minutes on low heat or until tender.
Remove skin and bones from chicken; cut into small pieces.
Slice green onion and olives into small pieces.

title: broccoli casserole(sans rice)
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add broccoli and cook until tender. Add mushroom soup, cheese, mushrooms and 3/4 cup almonds.
Pour in largest casserole available or in 2 casseroles.
Sprinkle rest of almonds and bread crumbs on top.
Bake in a 300° oven until bubbly.
Serves 18.

title: diet cheese cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then add pineapple.
Put in a 9-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Bake chicken, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Baste and cook for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Spread pineapple over cake.
Beat cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk.
Beat pudding with 2 cups milk.
Combine and spread over pineapple.
Top with 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups toasted coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toast coconut in 350° oven for 7 to 12 minutes.
Toss several times to get golden brown.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening. Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip, cottage cheese and pineapple.
Stir until softened.
Add mandarin oranges, marshmallows and pecan pieces. Stir together.
Add box of orange jello (dry) and stir together. Chill and keep in the refrigerator.
Better after a couple of hours.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Put all in Dutch oven.
Bake 5 hours at 275°.

title: 6 layer taco dip
directions: Peel, seed and mash avocados.
Stir in garlic, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Spread in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Carefully spread sour cream over mixture.
Drain piquant sauce well and pour over sour cream.
Top with layer of olives and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve with nacho chips.

title: cheesy turkey chowder
directions: Place turkey wing or drumstick in large saucepan.
Add water until meat is just covered.
Add salt and onion.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer until meat is tender.
Remove meat from broth; debone and cut meat into small pieces.
Set aside.
To 4 cups broth (add water to make 4 cups, if necessary), add carrots, celery and potatoes.
Simmer until tender.
Gradually blend milk into flour until smooth.
Stir into broth, along with butter and cheese.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add turkey meat.
This is very good with chicken meat, too.

title: ham delights(yield:  36 rolls)
directions: Using steel blade
of
food processor, chop ham finely. Remove to bowl,
chop
cheese
finely
and set aside.
Combine finely chopped
onion,
margarine,
mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Process.
Add poppy seed and process.
Split the whole package of rolls as
one large roll.
Spread both insides with onion mixture. Sprinkle ham
and cheese on one side of rolls. Put rolls together in original container and cut out individual rolls.
May
return to	original
plastic
bag,
cover and freeze.
When ready to serve,
preheat
oven to 375° and heat rolls for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tomato tofu pie
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add sauce, salt and pepper; stir 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add tofu and most of the cheese (save some for top).
Stir together and pour into a 9-inch round baking dish or pie crust.
Top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all above, allow to chill.	Add Rum* to own taste or serve as nonalcoholic punch.
Add cut up pieces of lemons, oranges, pineapple, limes and whole cranberries.
Serves 50.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Cut meat into strips, then dice.
Coat skillet or wok with oil; heat and break in eggs.
When partly cooked, stir in seasoning.
Add meat, soy sauce, rice, water chestnuts and celery. Stir together and continue cooking until rice barely begins to brown.
Add cut onions, including green tops in slices.
Stir into rice and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: great gravy for meatballs
directions: These ingredients mixed together are enough for each 1 1/2 pound of a meat mixture.
Added note:
15 pounds of meat ball mixture makes approximately 250 meatballs.

title: salad
directions: Combine peas, onions and cabbage, then add seeds and dressing just before serving.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix syrup
and sugar in saucepan and bring to boil.
As soon as sauce boils, stir in peanut butter.
Stir thoroughly. Butter a 9
x
13-inch
pan and place corn flakes and peanuts into pan. Pour
mixture
of
syrup
and sugar over flakes and nuts.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Place Doritos on bottom of baking dish.
Layer chicken over chips.
Mix soups, chicken broth and Ro-Tel together.
Pour on top of chips and chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo until tender.
Combine all other ingredients except cheese.
Mix good.
Pour into a greased oblong casserole dish.
Add cheese to top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter pies
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk, peanut butter and powdered sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts.
Refrigerate one hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: talarena
directions: Brown burger, onion, pepper and chili.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain grease.
Line the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with hamburger mixture.
Pat down with spoon.
Spread tomato soup over hamburger.
Cook noodles and drain.
Do not overcook noodles. Spread noodles over hamburger and soup.
Top with cheese slices all over top of pan.
Top with mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Put in a baked pie shell.
Top with 8 ounces Cool Whip.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Put cheese and salsa dip in a microwavable bowl.
Cook until cheese melts and can be mixed well.
Add beans and heat until well blended.
Serve warm and with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make into a ball.
Roll in pecans. Refrigerate.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Chop onion.
Saute in pan with 1 teaspoon butter or oil until clear.
Mix all ingredients together and heat.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Pare apples; slice and arrange in 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sift 1/2 cup sugar and 3/4 cup flour; cut in butter with a fork until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 40 minutes.

title: my favorite bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine first 7 ingredients including orange rind, if using.
Set aside.

title: the "best" brownies
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients.
Mix all remaining ingredients then combine all together.
Bake in a 9 inch square pan for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.
Brownies will be done when they pull away from the pan.
(You can double recipe and bake in a cake pan.)

title: brunswick stew
directions: Grind meat in food processor.

title: scuppernong ice cream
directions: Combine
juice	and
remaining	ingredients
in a large bowl; stir well.	Pour mixture into 1 gallon freezer, electric or hand turned.
Let ripen about 1 hour.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: ham croquettes
directions: Mix ham, oatmeal, milk and eggs.
Form into large balls or loaves.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream butter well; add both sugars gradually and beat for 1 minute.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat for 2 minutes.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, salt, baking soda, oatmeal and nutmeats. Add dry ingredients to the creamed mixture and mix until well blended.

title: aunt gloria's shrimp
directions: Clean shrimp.
Place in roasting pan (no shells).
Add white wine.
Slice butter on top.
Add bread crumbs and garlic.
Set oven to 300° to 350°.
They are ready when shrimp are pink and butter has melted.

title: horseradish dip
directions: Mix the ingredients and chill several hours.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook
first
3 ingredients to soft ball stage.	Combine the rest and form popcorn balls.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel and quarter eggplant.
Boil in salted water until tender. Drain and mash.
Brown meat.
Add onion, celery and green pepper. Cook for 10 minutes.
Add eggplant and remaining ingredients, except rice and water.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add cooked rice and water, if needed.
Cover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pink delight
directions: Mix the cherry pie filling.
Add the milk, then add the drained pineapple and Cool Whip, stirring well.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and garlic in large saucepan. Drain off excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Boil gently for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine in a large pan.
Add peanut butter, powdered sugar and Rice Krispies.
Mix until moist.
Make into balls (nut size).
Set aside.
In double boiler, melt remaining ingredients. Keep warm and dip balls into chocolate.
Makes 11 dozen.

title: waldorf slaw
directions: Toss all ingredients together.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Brush chicken with salad dressing.
Coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in covered container in the refrigerator.
Will keep for months.

title: salsa dip(low-fat)
directions: Put softened cream cheese in a medium bowl with salsa.
With mixer at medium speed, mix until well blended.
Serve with cut up raw vegetables or low-fat chips.

title: cherry muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, 3/4 cup sugar and salt.
Add drained cherries.
Toss to coat.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: In a large heavy skillet, heat the oil over moderately high heat.
Add onions, green pepper and celery; saute, stirring frequently, until onion is browned, about 15 minutes.
Add shrimp, salt and cayenne pepper.
Cook, stirring frequently, until shrimp turn pink, about 3 minutes.
Sprinkle the flour over the shrimp and toss well to coat.
Add 1/2 cup water and bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat and simmer for 2 minutes.
(If more gravy is desired, add another tablespoon of flour and an additional 1/2 cup water.)
Stir in Tabasco sauce and parsley.
Serve over rice.

title: butterscotch chocolate fudge
directions: Melt together the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Add the milk, then add the marshmallows.
Add the nuts and vanilla. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool.

title: health cookies
directions: Grease baking sheet lightly with shortening.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine.
Add sugars and cream well.
Beat eggs well and combine with creamed mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to other mixture.
Add oats, Rice Krispies, pecans and vanilla.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Form dough into balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake until light brown, about 8 minutes. Let stand on sheet until cool (suitable for freezing).

title: savory pot roast
directions: In 6 quart saucepan or electric skillet, in hot oil, brown roast on all sides.
When brown, spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup of water.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 2 hours or until roast is tender, turning meat every 30 minutes.
Add water when needed.
Remove roast.
Use remaining mixture as gravy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together, adding the cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Make cake as directed only use juice from cocktail instead of water. Bake as directed on package. When cool, top with Cool Whip.

title: maple-pecan cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and pour into medium skillet. Tightly cover skillet and set over medium (not hot) heat for 10 minutes.
When top surface of cake is firm, loosen edges and turn out onto serving plate.
Arrange pecan halves on top.
Pour 1/4 cup maple syrup over cake.
Pour on rest of syrup before serving. Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: easy casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
When done, let cool and set aside.
Make Stove top dressing according to directions on box.
Pull chicken off bone.
Put chicken in a layer in casserole dish.
Put dressing on top of chicken.
Mix soup with 1 can milk and stir until smooth. Pour over casserole.
Add bread crumbs to top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until warm.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix the last 6 ingredients together.
Cook carrots until fork-tender; cool.
Slice onion and bell pepper.
Put carrots in container, along with bell pepper and onion slices.
Pour marinade over vegetables and let marinate overnight.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Fold Cool Whip and milk together; do not whip or beat.
Add pineapple, lemon juice and nuts.
Pour into pie shells and chill thoroughly.

title: banana-peach shake
directions: Combine first three ingredients in container of an electric blender.
Cover and process until smooth. Makes 3 cups.

title: lime milk punch
directions: In mixing bowl or blender, blend ice cream with limeade. Gradually add milk and then food coloring.
Pour into punch bowl. Add sparkling water.
Float scoops of sherbet and lime slices on top.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Cook, drain and
mash potatoes.
Add eggs and butter and mix well. Add remaining ingredients and pour into casserole dish.

title: grandma's apple crisp
directions: Put apples in ungreased pan (9-inch).
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, lemon peel and nutmeg; mix well.
Add egg; stir until moistened. Spoon evenly over apples.
Drizzle butter over top.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 4 tablespoons sugar and place in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 4 to 6 minutes.
Cool.
Mix 8 ounces cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel mixture.
Mix jello, boiling water and strawberries.
Pour over second layer and chill until set.

title: mexican crinkle cookies
directions: Beat together shortening and sugar, then add egg, corn syrup and cocoa.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix until well blended.
Shape dough into small balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let stand on pan until top of cookie cracks, then remove.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine soup and milk in a rectangular dish.
Reserve a cup for the top of the chicken.
Add mushrooms, onion soup mix and rice.
Place chicken breasts on top of mixture; cover with foil. Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: grilled chicken breasts with chipotle-orange glaze(low calorie)
directions: Prepare a grill or preheat the broiler.
In a small bowl, whisk together orange juice concentrate, chipotles, vinegar, molasses and mustard.
Lightly oil the grill or broiler rack.
Season chicken with salt and grill or broil for 2 minutes.
Turn, brush with the orange glaze and cook for 4 minutes, brushing occasionally with glaze.
Turn again, brush with glaze and cook until center is no longer pink, 1 or 2 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet; top with nut or cherry.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix first 7 ingredients.
Put in a greased casserole dish; top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat ingredients 10 minutes on stove top.

title: betty brown
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter, sugar and eggs together. Add dry ingredients and beat.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch prepared pan.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: fried rice
directions: Use a deep, nonstick skillet, turn heat to high and preheat skillet.
Put in chilled rice and heat through, stirring constantly.
Add eggs and stir until eggs are cooked.
Add meat and vegetables.
Heat through.
Add soy sauce and margarine.
Heat still steaming and serve.
Serves 6.

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt the butter in saucepan and add sugar, nuts, egg and dates.
Stir and cook 10 minutes until thick and bubbly.
Cool lightly.
Add Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Roll into balls and in the coconut.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Put 1 can cream of celery soup and 1 soup can water in deep casserole dish.
Add raw potatoes, onions and cheese.
Stir and cover.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix together and let set, covered, for 1 day.
Mix several times during the day; enjoy.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and lay flat to cool on foil.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: holiday cake(a coronary delight)
directions: Mix apple, flour, sugar, nuts, raisins, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and soda and add vanilla, eggs and oil.
Grease a large Bundt pan or a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes (toothpick test) at 350°.

title: summer cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a large round pan to make 1 layer.
Cool.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Arrange fruit around edges and on top in a pretty design.
This cake is beautiful and delicious!
Everyone will want some!!

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger in a skillet. Add rest of ingredients and let come to a boil.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecued meatballs(club member: brad smith)
directions: Combine ingredients and form small meatballs. Dredge in flour and deep fry until done; drain well. Pour your favorite barbecue sauce over meatballs and serve warm.
These freeze well.

title: swiss steak mozzarella
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Coat with flour.
Melt margarine in skillet; brown meat slowly on both sides.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and basil; cover and simmer for 1 hour. Add green pepper and onions.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes longer or until meat is tender.
Top with cheese.
Cover and heat until cheese melts.
(The secret is to cook until tender.)

title: candied pecans
directions: Bring canned milk and sugar to boil over low flame.
Stir frequently.
Add cinnamon and stir.
Add pecans; stir until all are coated.
Spread on wax paper to cool, separating each half. Store in closed container.

title: pork chop and stuffing casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to directions.
Place in 9x13 inch pan.
Brown pork chops and place on top of stuffing.
Mix soup with milk and pour over chops and stuffing.
Bake at 350 degrees, covered, for 1 hour.

title: dynamite stuffed peppers
directions: Brown burger and onion together and drain off all fat.
In large bowl, combine rice, margarine, meat mixture, tomatoes, salt and basil and mix well.
Spoon filling into pepper shells and tamp down to make sure they are full.
Top with tomato sauce and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: gene's fruit cake
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in milk.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix together.
Use a bread loaf pan lined with foil.
Mold cake in pan. Pour sherry, brandy or rum over top.
Refrigerate 3 to 5 days.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread, egg and salt.
Shape into about 50 small meatballs. Brown slightly and drain all fat.
Cook onion and butter until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add meatballs to this and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: creamed chicken and biscuits
directions: Heat peas, chicken, soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper to boiling.
Prepare biscuits.
Pour chicken mixture over biscuits.

title: spring pea salad
directions: Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon bits with sour cream.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add walnuts and set aside.
Blend in blender the sugar, margarine, egg, bananas, and milk.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix until well moistened.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan.
Bake one hour or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and put	over 2/3 of dressing.
Save 1/3 for top.
Start with a layer
of squash, layer of onions, next mix sour cream, soup,
sauce
and
pimento.
Pour
this
over dressing, squash and onion mixture.
Sprinkle rest of dressing mix over.
Then bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans into pie shell, combine rest of ingredients and mix well with mixer.
Pour over pecans.
They will rise to the top while baking.
Bake on bottom rack of oven at 350° until firm, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine cereal, sugar, flour, salt and baking soda; mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs and oil.
Mix well, making sure all dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill paper lined muffin tins 2/3 full with batter.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes or until done.
Yield: 2 dozen muffins.

title: apple-oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients; stir in oats.
Combine liquid ingredients with apple; stir together until just moistened.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes in well-greased muffin tins.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: acorn cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together; add remaining ingredients except chocolate squares and mix well.
Shape like an acorn.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Melt chocolate and dip cookies in halfway.
Let dry on waxed paper.

title: puffy tuna bites
directions: Drain tuna; flake.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine with remaining ingredients except puff shells.
Cut tops from shells. Fill each with 2 teaspoons mixture.
Yields 30 appetizers.

title: quick quiche
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in one bowl until the eggs are well blended. Pour into a buttered deep pie pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean from the center.

title: dirt pie
directions: Cover bottom of pie plate or clean flower pot bottom with ground Oreo cookies.
Pour in filling.
Cover with remainder of cookies.
Refrigerate before serving.
Top with artificial flower or something light, so it won't stick in the pie.

title: brunch rolls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spoon into greased muffin pans. Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Serve while hot.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: steven's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix, then pour all ingredients into uncooked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Turn oven down to 300° for 30 to 45 minutes more.

title: lemon crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs. Dissolve ammonia in milk. Add sugar mixture. Add oil of lemon. Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead well. Roll to approximately 1/8-inch thick and cut into squares.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° until lightly browned on bottom (watch closely). Recipe makes a large batch.

title: corned beef picnic buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 muffin cups.
In
a bowl, combine corned beef, chili sauce, mayonnaise, pickle relish, onion and cheese. Separate refrigerated dough into triangles.
Place about 2 tablespoons corned beef mixture on each dough triangle near wide end.
Pull up sides of dough over filling. Roll to opposite point of triangle until filling is completely covered. Pinch edges to seal.
Place buns in greased muffin cups with point of dough on the bottom.
Brush tops with butter or margarine. Sprinkle potato chips over buns. Gently press chips into buns. Bake until lightly browned, about 20 minutes. Cool slightly on a rack.
Wrap warm buns in paper napkins or paper towels.
If buns will not be served within 3 hours, refrigerate.
Reheat buns on a baking sheet in a 350° oven 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple icebox pie
directions: Drain juice into a large pot. Add marshmallows and heat until melted. Let cool. Whip cream (with powdered sugar to taste). Add pineapple to juice/marshmallow mix. Fold in whipped cream. Pour into shell and refrigerate.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, cool, bone and dice.
Sprinkle on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cut up 1 large onion, sprinkle on top of chicken.
Add garlic salt and chili powder.
Grate 4 ounces Velveeta cheese and sprinkle on top.
Crush bag of Doritos, sprinkle on top, saving enough to sprinkle on top before baking.

title: noodles
directions: Beat egg yolks and whole egg until very light.
Beat in water, vinegar and salt.
Stir in flour; work in with hands.
Divide dough in 3 parts and roll as thin as possible (paper thin) on lightly floured board.
Let dry a while and cut in desired lengths.

title: loaf bread
directions: Mix the ingredients, then add 4 cups plain flour; mix well in a large bowl.
Let stand for 2 hours, then knead in flour.
Let stand for 15 to 20 minutes after you put in baking pans.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put vegetables in a gallon jar. Combine vinegar, sugar and salt. Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate. Keeps for several days.

title: hardees biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add flour last. Mixture will be slightly runny. Blend in self-rising flour for the texture you want. Bake at 400° to 425° for 8 to 9 minutes or until golden brown.

title: one skillet marinated chicken
directions: Combine dressing, wine and marinate chicken at least 2 hours. Remove chicken.
Save sauce.
Use 1/4 cup to baste chicken until done.
Remove and keep warm.
Add water, rice, and sauce.
Mix in electric skillet.
Bring to boil, then simmer until rice is done. Serves 4.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter or cocoa and oats. Spoon onto wax paper, or press onto greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Spray a 10 x 13-inch cake pan with a nonstick spray.
Spread cooked noodles evenly in bottom of pan.
In a separate bowl, mix soup and evaporated milk together until smooth.
Add parsley and basil.
Pour soup mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle chicken and celery over the pan evenly.
Stir gently, just enough to combine ingredients.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Beat eggs. Add mustard, milk and salt. Stir. Add bread and sausage. Pour in a 9 x 13 buttered baking pan. Top with cheese. Set in refrigerator overnight and bake in morning at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla. Mix until thick.
Add zucchini.
Mix.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix until smooth.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: mom's cream cheese dip
directions: Put onion and salt in a mixing bowl; add cream cheese and mix until creamy. Add eggs, pimento and green pepper and beat thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add enough mayonnaise or salad dressing to make creamy.
This recipe doubles or triples easily.
Just remember to refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put ingredients in
baking
pan. Put strips of bacon on top or butter,
1	can
tomato
sauce and enough water to make gravy and bake.

title: mini stromboli
directions: Place 3 slices of pepperoni on each roll and top with 1 tablespoon of cheese.
Fold and seal rolls.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: pecan pie crust
directions: Place all ingredients in a 9-inch pie plate; do not stir. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Stir mixture to blend well.
Firmly press mixture into bottom and sides of pie plate.
Cool.
Yield: one 9-inch pie shell ready for your favorite filling.
This recipe came from Southern Living.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat eggs slightly. Beat in both cheeses, flour, salt and pepper.
Drain broccoli well, patting dry with paper towels.
Stir into egg mixture.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Mix well for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a flat baking dish.

title: rocks(cookies)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Sift next 4 dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and chopped nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together well and put into greased casserole.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream Crisco and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Add unbeaten egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into balls, using a rounded teaspoon for each.
Roll balls in sugar and place on greased baking sheet.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and add eggs, peanut butter and sifted ingredients.
Roll in small ball and press with a fork.
Bake in oven at 375°, about 10 minutes.

title: meat and vegetable soup
directions: Brown veal lightly in heated butter in a 6-quart kettle.
Add onion and cook until limp.
Add salt, pepper, leek, potatoes, carrot, celery, tarragon, marjoram and water.
Bring to a boil and cover.
Reduce heat and simmer until veal is tender, 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: butterscotch goodies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter over low heat (or in microwave).
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal.
Drop
by spoonfuls onto a platter.
Refrigerate until it gets hard.

title: vegetable log
directions: Add all ingredients together (except nuts) with cream cheese. Form into 2 logs and roll in the chopped nuts.
Keep refrigerated until 15 to 30 minutes prior to serving with crackers.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well with electric mixer. Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar, add vanilla and eggs, beat well.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternatley with sour cream.
Drop onto greased and floured cookie sheets. Bake at 400° for 10-12 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: In mixer bowl, cream together sugar, shortening and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extract. Thoroughly stir together flour and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.

title: cajun meat pie
directions: *Start several hours or day before.

title: whipped cream potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with jackets on.
Cool.
Grate on large side of grater.
Put in casserole by layers, salt and butter.
Put on top paprika.
Pour unwhipped whipping cream on top.
Cover.
Let stand 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Break biscuits in quarters, dip in margarine and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in tube pan.
Pour any left over melted margarine over the top.

title: roasted corn-on-the-cob
directions: Stir together butter and salt; blend in herbs.
Keep butter soft.
Pull back corn husk; remove silks with a brush.
Place ear of corn on a piece of heavy-duty foil; brush with 1 tablespoon of the butter mixture.
Wrap up corn in foil.
Roast the corn directly on hot coals of grill until tender, turning frequently, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and butter in saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by spoon onto waxed paper.

title: corncob jelly
directions: Wash corncobs and cut into 4-inch lengths.
Place in container.
Add 2 quarts of water.
Bring to boil.
Heat and boil slowly for 35 to 40 minutes.
Strain the juice.
Measure out 3 cups of juice into a large container.
Add powdered pectin and bring to a boil.
Add sugar and again bring to boiling point. Boil 5 minutes.
Skim.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: courtney's marinated carrots
directions: Mix soup, vinegar, oil, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper together first, then add other ingredients and marinate in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.
Excellent side dish for meats.

title: peach or berry cobbler
directions: Mix all together.
Put in pan.
Drain fruit well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tasty cheese "grits"
directions: Bring water to a boil and add salt and slowly stir in grits. Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and cheese.
Put eggs in cup and add milk to make 1 cup measure.
Beat well and add grits mixture. Bake in greased 2-quart casserole at 300° for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Mix dry cake mix and cinnamon in large bowl.
Add eggs, water and oil. Blend, then beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Fold in zucchini.
Turn batter into pan and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Frost with vanilla frosting when fully cooled.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: chili
directions: Brown turkey, onions, peppers and garlic.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer in saucepan over low heat or in crock-pot, stirring occasionally for at least 1/2 hour. the longer, the better the flavor.
This is a mild chili.
For a hotter chili, add green chili peppers, jalapeno or habanero peppers to make 5 Alarm Chili.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix peanut butter with margarine.
To this, add sugar. Mix in cereal (you may have to mix with your hands).
Mold this mixture into small balls.
Melt paraffin in the top of double boiler. When melted, add semi-sweet chocolate pieces.
Dip each ball into chocolate; lift out with fork.

title: marilyn's lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne and drain.
Cook hamburger and drain.
Add tomato sauce and simmer.
Mix cottage cheese, sour cream and green onions (chopped) to taste, all together.
Add half cheese.
Put hamburger and tomato sauce mixture, then lasagne, then cottage cheese mixture.
Layer it in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer for 8 minutes.
Add a little more milk if reheating the soup.

title: ruby's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In a 10-inch cast-iron skillet, melt butter. Add brown sugar and stir. Arrange drained sliced pineapple on top of sugar. Fill in with well drained, crushed pineapple. Add cherries into center of pineapple slices, anywhere else for color.
Mix yellow cake mix as instructed except substitute juice for water.
Pour batter on top of the pineapple/sugar.
Bake in oven approximately 15 minutes longer than cake mix instructions call for at the same temperature (usually 350°).
Remove from oven.
Place a large serving plate over skillet.
Carefully turn the two upside down. The cake will drop out easily onto the plate!

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Will make approximately 6 crab cakes.
Fry on medium heat with very little oil or a nonstick covered pan, approximately 20 minutes.
Serve on bun or on plate with mixed vegetables.

title: cheesy chicken pitas(this is a lo-cholesterol recipe)
directions: Toss peppers and onion in a small bowl.
Spray small skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Add chicken and garlic and cook over medium heat until tender.
Spread each bread half with mustard. Fill with chicken, two cheese halves and 1/4 cup pepper mixture. Cover loosely and microwave on High 30 seconds or until cheese melts.
Add shredded lettuce.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Peel potatoes and slice about 1/8-inch thick.
Place slices in a bowl with oil, salt, pepper and oregano. Toss to mix well.
Place slices in greased 15 x 10 x 1 baking pan. Spread slices so they overlap slightly.
Bake potatoes uncovered for about 20 minutes; longer if you prefer them to be crispier.

title: chicken tremendose
directions: Grease pan.
Sprinkle rice in pan and then lay in chicken. Sprinkle with onion soup mix and bouillon mixture.
Pour chicken soup diluted with water over.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Bake uncovered another 15 minutes.
Add water if necessary.

title: custard pie
directions: Bake in pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° until done.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Cream softened cheese with butter in small bowl.
Add sugar and cornstarch and beat.
Add egg, milk and vanilla and beat at high speed until creamy.
Set aside.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and orange Jello well.
Add remaining ingredients and chill before serving.

title: cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a saucepan, cook pudding and milk over medium heat until thickened. Cool slightly. In a bowl, cut peanut butter into confectioners sugar until small crumbs form. Add additional sugar, if necessary. Set aside 2 tablespoons crumbs. Sprinkle remaining mixture into pie shell. Pour pudding over crumbs. Chill. Top with whipped cream. Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top. Makes 1 pie.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Put tomatoes in blender with the flour.
Then add the onions, garlic and all the other ingredients.
Simmer gently, uncovered, until slightly thickened and creamy, about 2 hours.
Stir frequently.

title: bacon and potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; cube and cook bacon for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: baked custard
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine first 5 ingredients; blend well.
Pour in custard cups (about 6) and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set in baking pan with about 1-inch hot water; bake 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend together until thick the first 3 ingredients.
To the egg mixture, add flour and baking powder and blend.
Pour over baked crust and return to oven.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Wash blueberries and put in a greased casserole.
Mix sugar, flour and eggs.
Spread this mixture over blueberries.
Melt butter and pour over entire mixture.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: snicker salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
For best results, chill overnight.
Feeds 20 plus.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add butter or margarine and cut in until crumbly.
Beat egg slightly and mix with milk; add to dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Knead until smooth, about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Heat, stirring, until shortening is melted and sugar and salt is dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in yeast until dissolved. Blend eggs into yeast mixture. Add flour gradually, beating well after each addition.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll each part out to a 9-inch circle. Cut each circle into 12 wedges. Roll wedges up, starting at large end. Arrange in crescent shapes on greased baking pan.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Brush with butter.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400° or until light brown. Remove from oven and brush with butter. Makes 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugars, eggs, vanilla and peanut butter.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Press down on top with floured fork or potato masher.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.

title: unusual oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat well.
In a separate mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients
gradually, mixing with hands, if necessary.
Shape the very stiff dough into small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet two inches apart.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: potato soup
directions: In medium saucepan, heat butter and oil until butter is melted. Add onion and garlic, cook, stirring often, 5 to 7 minutes or until onion is soft.
Add potatoes, turnip, chicken broth and seasonings.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes and turnips are fork-tender.
In blender, process soup in batches until pureed. Return to saucepan.
Stir in cream and cook about 5 minutes. Pour into serving dishes. Yields 5 1/2 cups.

title: carrot bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
In a mixing bowl combine oil, sugars, eggs.
Then beat until well blended.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350 oven for 1 hour or until done.
Cool, slice and spread with cream cheese.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Heat first four ingredients until butter melts. Remove from heat and add bread cubes.
This may be done ahead of baking time. When ready to serve, place in a 350° oven.
Bake for 15 minutes. Take out and stir.
Bake another 15 minutes, covered.

title: chicken melody
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together soup, mayo and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat.
Prepare stuffing according to package.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange cooked broccoli over stuffing.
Do the same with chicken.
Pour soup mixture over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: in-croud grooves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cream together margarine, sugar, butter flavoring and flour until crumbly.
Spread and press evenly into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
While mixture is baking, beat eggs, vanilla and other extracts and brown sugar.
Sift together flour, brown sugar, salt and baking powder, then stir.
Add coconut and pecans; mix well.
Pour over the baked cookie layer.
Return to oven and continue baking for about 30 minutes.
Cool for about 2 hours before cutting into bars.

title: stromboli
directions: Take sausage out of skin and cook it.
Then crumble it up and divide it in 5 portions.
Roll the dough out on a floured surface (flour rolling pin, too).
Spread the sausage in the middle of the dough.
Season with garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Use 6 slices of cheese for each dough.
Fold over the ends of dough and pinch like for pastie.
If dough doesn't seal, sprinkle with a little water and pinch again.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: miracle whip cream cheese cake
directions: Mix together lemon jello, boiling water and lemon juice.
Let cool.
Add sugar to jello mixture.
Add cream cheese that has been creamed well to mixture.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion, green chilies, garlic and Worcestershire sauce in 1-quart microproof casserole.
Cover and cook on High for 3 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Cover and cook until cheese is melted, stirring once.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: jane johnson's chicken mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup broth.
Heat rest of broth and mix with plain gelatin and the remaining 1/2 cup broth.
Mix with other ingredients and mold in one large mold, individual molds or muffin tins lined with paper inserts.

title: sour cream chicken breasts
directions: Combine sour cream, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, paprika and lemon juice; add chicken.
Marinate overnight.
Coat heavily with sour cream mixture and roll in Italian bread crumbs.
Drizzle with 1/2 cup melted butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy curry dip
directions: Mix well and chill in covered bowl.
Wonderful served with cubes of ham, chicken, turkey, chilled shrimp, apple wedges or grapes.

title: instant rice and gravy
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add instant rice.
Stir.
Cover and remove from heat.
Wait 5 minutes and serve.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and spices.
Add sugar.
Stir in molasses and water.
Add flour, soda and salt to molasses mix.
Chill for several hours.
Roll to 1/8-inch diameter on greased sheet and bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into bite size balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve hot with party picks.

title: traci's marinated chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Cook chicken on grill, basting frequently.

title: mediterranean shrimp
directions: In a large skillet combine olive oil and garlic.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until garlic is golden but not browned.
Remove and discard garlic.
Add shrimp and saute just until they turn pink.
Pour in wine, increase heat to high and boil 5 minutes.
Remove shrimp with slotted spoon and set aside. Continue to cook wine until reduced by half.
Add tomatoes, olives, parsley and salt; cook sauce 5 minutes more.
Return shrimp to skillet and heat through.
Blend in Tabasco.

title: mahogany cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and cream again, beat eggs in this mixture, add coffee.
Sift the dry ingredients, flour, cocoa, soda and salt and add a little at a time, lastly the vinegar and vanilla.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Celery, giblets and boiled eggs can be added, if desired. Pour into crock-pot and cook on high until crusty around edges, approximately 2 1/2 hours.
Do not stir.

title: mama's baked beans
directions: Cook onion in bacon drippings until tender. Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue chicken arms
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chicken).
Marinate chicken in this sauce overnight in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch nut torte
directions: Beat egg yolks well, add sugar, baking powder and flavorings. Beat egg whites enough to hold a peak.
Fold into yolks, then add crumbs and nuts.
Make into two 9-inch layers or use large cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool cake.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
In bread machine, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt and sugar.
Start mixer on dough setting.
Add flour gradually.
Mix for 5 minutes. Roll pieces of dough on floured counter.
Stretch and shape.
Place on cookie sheet.
Beat the egg and brush some on top to make golden.
Sprinkle with salt and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.	Top with melted butter and more salt or sugar and cinnamon.

title: roast beef au jus
directions: Place roast in ovenproof dish; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce over roast; it will drip down to bottom of dish.
Use enough sauce to have 1/4 to 1/2 inch of liquid in dish. Place cut up onion on roast.
Cover and cook at 350° to desired doneness. The natural juices will blend with the sauces to form a thin gravy for serving over the meat.

title: crazy cake
directions: Put
ingredients in large bowl in order given.	Mix all together
before adding the boiling water.	Beat well and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Double for two layers.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour and salt. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook in microwave until mixture begins to thicken.
Add egg yolks and cook until thick.
Remove from microwave and add butter, vanilla and coconut.
After cools, pour mixture into baked pie shell and spread meringue on top.
Bake in oven until meringue is brown.

title: turkey or chicken dressing
directions: Cook chicken and use broth to mix stuffing mix and croutons. Mix onions, salt, pepper, eggs and hamburger (if desired).
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: aunt leslie's hollandaise sauce
directions: Squeeze lemon juice from plastic lemon into equal parts of mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add dry mustard.
Stir.
Bring to soft bubble (the longer it cooks, the thicker it gets).

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, oleo and cream cheese.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the cake flour and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into tube pan.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butterscotch icing
directions: Combine the shortening, salt and xxx sugar into a large bowl, adding the sugar gradually and creaming well.
Put aside.
Combine brown sugar, butter, 1/4 cup milk and corn syrup in a saucepan and cook until a small amount forms a hard ball in cold water (250°), stirring constantly after the mixture starts to boil.
Quickly heat 3 tablespoons milk and add to the first mixture, then gradually pour in the cooked mixture.
Beat until thick and smooth enough to spread on 2 (8-inch) cakes or 1 (10-inch) loaf cake. Frost quickly as this thickens rapidly.
A hot spreader helps.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt in a large cooking utensil.
Cook briskly, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes, or until candy thermometer registers 210°.
Add butter and pecans. Cook and stir constantly for 5 minutes, or until candy reaches 230° or candy forms soft ball in water.
Remove from heat.
Beat until mixture loses it's gloss, then drop in mounds on waxed paper.
If mixture hardens too fast, warm pan a minute or two over low heat. When cool, store in covered container.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Preheat oven broiler. In a large skillet, saut garlic and ham in butter over medium heat for 2 minutes. Add cauliflower. Stir and cook until tender but still crisp. In a small bowl, combine cream, flour, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper. Blend well with whisk. Slowly stir flour mixture into skillet. Cook and stir until thickened. Simmer 1 additional minute. Pour into a 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Place under broiler until lightly browned, about 2 to 4 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in large container.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Add lemonade and pineapple juice.
Chill before serving time.
Add almond extract and ginger ale to taste.
Yield:
30 to 50 servings.

title: seven layer casserole(from 1975 edition)
directions: Place ingredients in casserole in order listed.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 30 more minutes to brown bacon.
If bacon is not used, bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a measuring cup, combine milk and eggs.
Stir in butter and vanilla. Pour into flour mixture.
Stir quickly with a fork just until mixed.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts, being careful to stir as little as possible.
Pour into 16 or 18 greased muffin tins. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve warm, if desired.

title: healthy muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine oats, flours, brown sugar, Oat Bran, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add raisins, dates and nuts.
Stir to coat with flour mixture.
Add milk, oil and egg whites; stir just until moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Lightly grease 12 muffin cups.
Spoon batter into cups, filling cups full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes, or until done.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.

title: beef-a-roni
directions: Brown and drain ground beef; add salt and pepper to taste. Saute chopped onion and celery.
Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions.
In a 9 x 13-inch or larger dish, mix meat, onions, celery, macaroni and cheese and tomatoes (undrained). Stir to mix well.
Smooth out and lay cheese slices over the mixture.
Bake at 350° until the mixture boils and the cheese melts.
Serve.

title: squirrel jambalaya
directions: Cut squirrel into serving pieces and season well.
Saute in oil until brown; remove from skillet.
Saute onions, celery, garlic, green peppers and parsley in oil until wilted.
Put squirrel in until tender.
Add rice and water.
Stir thoroughly. Add salt, cook slowly about 30 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: never fail cherry pie
directions: Drain water pack cherries well (press out part of excess liquid).
Mix with can of pie filling.
Add all ingredients, mixing well.

title: turkey-noodle poppy seed casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain well and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter in a Dutch oven until tender; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in noodles, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and next 4 ingredients; add pimiento and stir gently.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients except cabbage leaves.
Put small amount on cabbage leaf and roll into bundle; hold with a toothpick.
Bake or boil.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets (not too mushy).
Cool, peel and grate them into baking dish.
Heat other ingredients together until cheese melts.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spicy carrots
directions: Combine ingredients in microwave dish.
Sprinkle with Tony's to taste.
Top with margarine.
Cover the dish; cook on High for about 10 minutes, then stir.
Cook until desired tenderness is reached (about 8 to 10 more minutes).

title: beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Combine beef, onion, salt, pepper, garlic powder and oregano in large skillet.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until beef is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, corn, peas and soups. Mix well.
Bring to boiling. Cover and lower heat.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix meat and soups, rice, water, salt and pepper together; pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
At that time, top with onion rings and brown, then ready to serve.
Can serve with a salad.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in square pan at 300° for 1 hour.
(Double the ingredients for the oblong baking pan.)

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except blueberries.
Fill paper cups 1/2 full and put blueberries on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In large, 6-quart soup pot, saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add chicken broth and spaghetti.
Heat for 5 minutes on medium. Add milk, broccoli and garlic.
Cook 5 more minutes. Add cheese.
Serve when cheese is melted and spaghetti noodles are tender.
Add extra broth or milk if soup is too thick.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain.
Add corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onion.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs or crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or can be cooked in microwave.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom

title: apple cake
directions: In mixing bowl, mix well vegetable oil, eggs and sugar.
In another bowl, mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to liquids; mix well.
Fold in chopped apples and chopped pecans.

title: seafood salad
directions: Drain the seafood well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss carefully and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Serve on lettuce, if desired.

title: cheese straw hors d'oeuvres
directions: Stir ingredients into a soft dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake on cookie sheets about 7 minutes at 450° (preheat oven).

title: cream cheese cups
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla, eggs and cream cheese until well blended. Add sour cream.
Line muffin pans with foil baking cups.
Place vanilla wafer in bottom of each cup.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350°.
Cool.
Top with prepared pie filling.

title: grandpa's dope(hot fudge)
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa powder and salt.
Add enough milk to make a thick liquid.
Stir in Karo syrup.
Bring to boil and boil until thick bubbles appear.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup butter to form crust.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together in a casserole dish.
Use bread crumbs or crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coco-cola salad
directions: Heat juice from pineapple and cherries. stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add the rest of ingredients and refrigerate.

title: iowa corn relish
directions: Boil corn 5 minutes.
Plunge into cold water.
Cut kernels from cobs.
Combine all ingredients; simmer 20 minutes.
Pack into clean, hot pint jars leaving 1 inch headspace.
Make certain vinegar solution covers vegetables.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling hot water bath 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough onto a pizza pan. Poke holes in dough with a fork. Bake as directed on cookie dough package. Cool completely.

title: easy cheese bread
directions: Combine Bisquick, cheese (grated) and poppy seed.
Add egg and milk and mix vigorously for 1 minute.
Spoon into lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix well cranberry sauce and drained pineapple.
Heat pineapple juice and enough water to make 2 cups.
Dissolve Jello in hot liquid.
Mix with fruit.
Put in 8 x 8 pan or 2 loaf pans.

title: coney sauce
directions: Combine everything except hot dogs until thick and simmer.
Add ground hot dogs and simmer 10 additional minutes.
Serve on hot dogs (with buns) and top with mustard and chopped onion, if desired.

title: party ham biscuits
directions: Heat the margarine, poppy seed, mustard and Worcestershire sauce in a saucepan.
Split rolls.
Place ham and cheese on rolls. With a pastry brush, brush mixture on rolls.
Heat at 325° for 15 minutes. Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Bake chicken in oven or microwave.
Cool and shred or cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook rice according to package directions. Precook broccoli in microwave, covered, for 4 minutes on High. Mix soups, water and 2/3 of cheese together.
Place rice in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour 1/2 of soup mixture over rice.
Place shredded chicken over soup.
Place broccoli on top of chicken.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over broccoli.
Spread remaining soup mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Add salad and homemade bread for a great meal.

title: indian curry(made with chicken, lamb or shrimp)
directions: Simmer chicken with celery, onions, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper. When chicken is done, debone and set aside. Drain the broth and save to use later. In the same pot, place butter, 2 medium chopped onions, garlic and apple. Add curry powder, mustard, flour and salt. Cook slowly for a few minutes. Add the chicken broth and simmer for about an hour.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot on high until jelly melts, stirring occasionally.
Leave in crock-pot and set on low setting to serve.

title: doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Combine sugar, flour and milk. Stir until smooth. Stir in yeast. Cover and let rise. Stir in eggs, margarine, sugar, salt, nutmeg and enough flour so mixture can no longer be stirred with a spoon. Cover and let rise.

title: brown-eyed randy's
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and salt. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make thumbprint in center.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in a 375° oven. When cool, fill thumbprint hole with the following frosting.

title: grandmother walter's caramel cake
directions: Grease and flour two
9-inch
round
cake
pans.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add
flour
and
buttermilk,
alternately. Dissolve soda in water and add
to
cake
mixture.
Beat well; add vanilla. Fill pans halfway with batter.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Allow to
cool completely before icing with Grandmother Walter's Icing.

title: tetrazzini
directions: Mix the cheeses and sour cream together in a large bowl; set aside.
Cook spaghetti.
Brown beef and fry onions together.
Add spaghetti sauce and mushrooms; simmer for about 7 minutes.
Drain the spaghetti and mix it with cheese mixture.
Spread it in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Pour sauce over it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pear delight
directions: Combine pears and sugar; place in a pie plate.
Cut butter into flour and sprinkle evenly over pears.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon.
Do not use mixer. Batter will be stiff.
Spread into floured and greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: butterscotch slices
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add nuts, vanilla and lemon.
Then add flour; mix well. Shape into 2-inch rolls in wax paper.
Chill overnight.
Cut in 1-inch slices.
Bake 5 or 6 minutes at 425°.

title: devil wings
directions: You will need 1 (2 gallon) resealable freezer bag.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Blend in 2 cups of flour.
Coat fruit and nuts with remaining 2 cups of flour.
Fold in fruit.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in all other ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in loaf pan.

title: perfect corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9x9x2-inch Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ham supreme with broccoli
directions: Break or cube bread and line bottom of casserole.
Layer remaining ingredients over bread.
Start with ham and top with broccoli, then cheese.
Pour eggs over layers and milk over all. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: russian spicy tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 1 or 2 teaspoons to a cups of hot water.

title: brownie supreme
directions: Bake the two packages of brownie mix by the instructions. While this is baking make your pudding according to the directions, which will take two cups milk. When the pudding has set up good, add 8 oz. of Cool Whip, and the almond extract and mix well. Set this in refrigerator. Take brownies and cut into small pieces. Place a layer of brownies in pan or bowl, next place Heath candy pieces and walnuts.

Pour pudding mixture over this. Then take the remaining Cool Whip and spread a layer over top and garnish with Heath candy pieces and walnuts. Instead of just having one layer, you could divide out and do another layer repeating the steps again.

title: sue's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on box.
Drain, rinse with cold water to cool, drain again.
Add cut up vegetables and Ranch dressing.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and black pepper and mix together.
Chill before serving.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Steam broccoli just until bright green.
Drain on paper towels.
Mix broccoli, onion, pepper and cheese in deep pie plate. Beat or blend remaining ingredients until smooth and pour over vegetable mixture.
Bake until golden brown, 30 to 40 minutes. Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with wooden spoon. Shape into balls. Place on jelly roll pan; bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Freeze well.

title: spring rice salad
directions: Gently mix rice with eggs, celery, onions and dill pickles. Fold in mayonnaise and salt.
Serve on lettuce leaves; garnish with tomato wedges or radish roses.
Stuffed olives may be used instead of pickles.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In a heavy 4 quart saucepot, cook bacon, 2-3 minutes over moderate low heat, stirring occasionally, until just golden brown. Add onion & garlic.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring often until onion is translucent.
Stir in broth, tomatoes, (break them up as you stir them in), vegetables, macaroni, basil, pepper.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in beans, cook 2 minutes.
Skim off foam.
Serve. Garnish with parsley or cilantro.
Serve with Parmesan cheese on the side.
Makes 7 cups.

title: likker sweet potatoes
directions: Mix
all together except "likker".
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven in a buttered 2 quart (9 x 13-inch) pan.

title: oven barbecue venison
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Roll prepared venison in mixture. Fry in small amount of shortening until brown on each side. Cover bottom of casserole dish with barbecue sauce.
Place lid on casserole dish and cook in 300° oven for 45 minutes to one hour. Add more sauce if needed.
(Chicken may be used instead of venison.)

title: easy cobbler
directions: Pour peaches in casserole dish.
Crumble dry cake mix over top.
Melt butter and drizzle over top of dry cake mix.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until top starts to get brown.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Shake milk and flour in jar until smooth.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in milk/flour mixture, parsley, Tabasco, celery seed, curry powder, onion salt and salt.
Simmer until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in crab meat.
Heat to serving temperature.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli with cheese sauce(microwavable recipe)
directions: Total cooking time: 18 minutes 45 seconds.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs very lightly.
Add all other ingredients and blend. Fold into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a slow oven (300°) for 45 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: chicken cacciatore
