directions: Cut chicken into serving portions and brown in hot olive oil. Add onions, peppers and garlic; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer one half hour or until chicken is tender. Serves 6.

title: hot chicken-rice salad
directions: Make the day before serving.
Combine all ingredients in a casserole.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Remove one hour before you plan to serve.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips and bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: company corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oleo until wilted.
Add the cooked rice.
Add beaten egg, pimento, sugar and both cans of corn. Mix well.
Add ham, if desired, and mix well.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 2-quart dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch) at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, chocolate chips, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.

title: pork roast
directions: Flour, salt and pepper and skillet brown all sides of roast. Cook in water for 3 to 4 hours until tender.
Take out of juice. Bake at 300° to 350° for 15 to 30 minutes.
While cooking in oven, put maple syrup on roast.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Melt butter and syrup.
Let ice cream set out for a few minutes to get soft.
Sprinkle almost all the cookies in the bottom of cake pan; pour butter on top.
With your hands, mix up the cookies and butter to make a "crust".
Put 1st layer of ice cream (spread with hands).
Pour the whole jar of syrup on top. Spread next layer of ice cream.
Spread container of whipped cream, then sprinkle remainder of cookies on top.

title: brownie muffin
directions: Melt butter, chocolate and vanilla in saucepan.
Mix flour, sugar and eggs.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Add nuts.
Do not overmix.
Makes 18 large or 36 small muffins.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes for small or 30 minutes for large muffins.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Take all ingredients except egg noodles and place in a pot of water and bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat approximately 45 minutes.
Remove the chicken from the pot and discard the bones. Place the chicken back into the pot with the noodles.
Heat to a boil and allow the noodles to cook for 15 minutes.

title: christine's no-roll sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat sugar and softened butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
In a small bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture, mixing well.
Dough will be sticky. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Brush pie shell slightly with beaten white from 1 egg.
Add rest of white to remaining eggs.
Beat slightly. Scald milk.
Pour over combined eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into pie shell. Bake in preheated oven at 425° about 25 minutes or until set. Cool.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs slightly, beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: spaghetti squares
directions: Cook spaghetti as package directs.
Beat egg well.
Mix with milk.
Place spaghetti in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour milk and egg over spaghetti.
Layer spaghetti sauce and pepperoni.
Top with cheese. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Stir all ingredients together with a fork until moistened.
Beat 1 minute.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Then, loosen and remove bread from pan.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla together.
Add corn flakes, oats, flour, soda, baking powder, salt and pecans.
Stir well.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix onion, sugar and applesauce with sauerkraut. Pour into baking dish. Lay chops around top of sauerkraut. Bake 300 degrees for 2 1/2 hours.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan. Top with icing.

title: orange blossom special cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: jewish brownies
directions: Mix the first six ingredients by hand.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel, cube, steam eggplant until tender.
Saute hamburger, sausage, onion (chopped) and celery sliced thinly.
Mix together in casserole with stewed tomatoes.
Top with lots of Cheddar, Mozzarella or Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hermit cookies
directions: Mix into bowl, shortening and brown sugar.
Sift flour.
Add soda, salt and spices.
Blend flour mixture into brown sugar mixture.
Mix in raisins.
Add egg and water.
Mix with fork to form stiff dough.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: granny's german hasenpfeffer
directions: Combine vinegar, water, salt, pepper and sugar.
Put rabbit pieces in a glass dish or crock.
Pour vinegar mixture over rabbit and lay on onion rings.
Make sure you have enough liquid to cover rabbit.
Cover with glass plate
or foil; refrigerate 12 hours (2 days won't hurt).
Remove rabbit and put in pan to cook.
Make a weaker mix of vinegar, water, sugar, salt and fresh onion.
Put 1 tablespoon of pickling spice in cheesecloth or gauze.
Make a tie at top in shape of ball with string.
Cook rabbit until tender over medium heat.
Do not boil.
Thicken with cornstarch to make a thin gravy.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar, creaming well.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Press pecan half into center of each.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Makes approximately 24.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in a small amount of water in saucepan for 8 minutes or until tender; drain.

Stir in mixture of soup, sour cream and water chestnuts. Add salt and pepper to taste. Combine margarine and stuffing mix in bowl. Toss to mix. Cover bottom of buttered 8 x 12-inch baking dish with half the stuffing mixture. Spoon in squash mixture. Top with remaining stuffing mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: honeyed walnut squares
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
At low speed, blend in flour until dough forms. Blend in walnuts.
Spread evenly in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 325°
until golden brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Cut into 25 squares.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix pineapple and dry pudding together.
Add sour cream and 1/2 cup Cool Whip; fold with pineapple and pudding.
Blend well. Pour into graham cracker pie shell; top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight or 4 to 5 hours.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Bake at about 350°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Yield: about 6 dozen.

title: baked chicken dish
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place the dry rice into baking dish. Mix together the dry soup mix, cream of chicken soup, water, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over rice; stir to mix well.
Add chicken.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil.
Cool.
Add confectioners sugar (more or less, to desired consistency).
Add vanilla.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Shape into rolls, about 2 1/2-inches in diameter.
Chill well or freeze.
Slice about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: In a 5-quart pot over medium heat, combine oil, onion, celery and garlic.
Saute until tender or onion is limp.
Stir in bouillon cubes, water and tomatoes with liquid.
Add carrots, cauliflower, lima beans, marjoram, thyme and pepper.
Cook 15 minutes, uncovered, then add ziti and cook another 15 minutes.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add melted chocolate, then eggs, beating well.
Add sifted flour, salt and baking powder alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in vanilla, pecans and coconut. Bake in three 9-inch pans for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cornish hens with fruited rice dressing
directions: Marinate raisins in sherry for 15 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet; add and dissolve bouillon cubes.
Add celery, onions and parsley.
Cook until tender.
Add rice, orange peel, salt, thyme and marinated raisins.
Toss lightly.
Sprinkle hens inside and out with salt and pepper to taste.
Rub with melted butter.
Fill cavity of each hen with 1/2 cup stuffing.
Truss and tie.

title: creamy pumpkin pie(no-bake)
directions: Put all ingredients except Cool Whip into bowl. Mix well. Add Cool Whip; stir. Pour into baked piecrust or graham cracker crust. Refrigerate. NO COOKING. DO NOT MIX pudding first. Pour dry mix into bowl with the other ingredients. Can top with Streusel Topping.

title: honey fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Tuck romaine leaves around fruit in bowl for garnish.

title: old-fashioned custard
directions: Beat eggs and stir in sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in slow oven for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean, at 325°.
Place dish in pan of water before putting in oven, then serve.

title: savannah red rice
directions: Cut sausage and bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Saute together in a large Dutch oven to render fat.
Drain fat.
Return meat to pan and add onion, celery and bell pepper.
Saute about 3 minutes on medium-high, stirring often.
If tomatoes are whole, chop and add entire contents to mixture along with water, rice and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook on top of stove for 10 minutes on medium-low.
Pour into a large greased (Pam) casserole dish.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage and chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: rocks
directions: Cook raisins and 1 cup water together until almost dry.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add soda to lukewarm raisins.
Mix rest of ingredients as usual.
Chill.
Make into small balls.
Dip in sugar.
Bake until light brown in 350° oven.

title: easy poppy seed cake
directions: Cover
poppy
seed
with the 1 cup of boiling water and soak 5
or
10 minutes.
Drain well, using fine tea strainer. Discard the hot water.
Combine the first five ingredients and beat
well with
mixer for 5 to 6 minutes.
Pour into 2 well-greased
and floured
9-inch
cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Split
each
layer
and fill with lemon
pudding
and pie filling, mixed as directed on package. Pudding
should
also be
cooled
completely before spreading between layers.
Pecans or
coconut
may
be
added on top of cake.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar. Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture and mix well. Chill 2 or 3 hours. Roll out on lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut with cookie cutter. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake in oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and seasoned salt in one bowl.
Mix eggs and milk in another bowl.
Dip each tomato slice into the milk mixture, then into the flour, back to the milk and then to the flour again, coating well.
Heat oil in a deep fryer to 350°.
Add battered tomato slices, a few at a time, and cook for 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Can also be cooked in a heavy skillet.
You can substitute cracker crumbs for the flour or cornmeal.

title: sister jill's cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Make chewy brownie mix and spread in a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 35 minutes until just set.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger and sausage together.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Brown evenly in skillet. Save the drippings.
In crock-pot, put all cans of mushroom soup.
Add the meatballs and drippings.
Stir and simmer 1 hour on low.
Stir occasionally.
(If you like more gravy, add another can of soup.)

title: fat-free marinara sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.
Pour over pasta.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: no cook blueberry freezer jam
directions: A word of advice; do not give it.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Line a 10 or 11-inch pie plate with pie crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over crust.
Saute onion, pepper and zucchini in 3 tablespoons oil until tender.
Brown eggplant, sliced into skillet.
Drain vegetables.
Arrange vegetables, including tomatoes and cooked vegetables in pie shell.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Dot with butter and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and peach juice in large bowl at low speed.
Melt the 1/2 stick of Parkay in a large, oblong pan.
Pour mixture in pan, then add the drained peaches.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tangy sweet sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Stir in hot dogs; heat to boiling.
Simmer until heated through.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple	and
juice
in	large
Pyrex
dish (9 x 13-inches).
Mix apples with lemon juice, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Spread
over
pineapple.	Sprinkle
dry cake mix over top.
Sprinkle
with
nuts.
Slice margarine or butter in thin pats
and
cover entire pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.	Serve warm, with whipped cream, if desired.
(May be made day before and heated.) Makes 15 servings.

title: buttermilk pancakes a-plenty
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside. Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add oil and sugar to yolks; mix with mixer.
Add flour mixture along with buttermilk to beaten yolks.
Fold in egg whites; bake on hot griddle or use for waffles.
There will be lots; save leftover batter for the next day.

title: oriental salad
directions: Combine oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper in a pan; bring to a boil and cook over medium-high heat until sugar is dissolved. Pour hot oil mixture over drained vegetables and oranges.
Mix well and chill.

title: beulah's red jello salad
directions: Stir all ingredients, except red jello, into the cooled orange or lemon jello mixture.
Put in refrigerator.
When set, pour one package of prepared and cooled red jello over the top and chill until set.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and chill for several hours. Serve with crackers.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in lemon peel.
Mash banana thoroughly and combine with wet ingredients.
Pour into greased muffin tins; fill 2/3 full.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: venison on rice
directions: Crisp bacon, set on paper towels to drain then crumble. Place the venison in the hot bacon grease and brown quickly.
Add everything to the venison and simmer 1 hour.
Then serve over rice.

title: lemon and lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-Os in hot water.
In separate bowl, mix milk and mayonnaise.
Add cottage cheese and crushed pineapple.
Then add nuts, mix all very good.
Add the Jell-O.
Put in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut acorn squash in half; clean seeds out.
Place on cookie sheet with shell sides up.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°. Test, using fork method, to determine if done.
If you can easily poke through shell, it is done.
Take out of oven; turn shells over.
Salt and pepper to taste; fill with butter and brown sugar. Put back in oven for approximately 10 minutes.
Remove squash from shells, mash slightly with potato masher and serve.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
Drain and serve on a bed of chopped lettuce or spinach.

title: sausage 'n bean bake
directions: Cook beans according to directions; drain.
Cook sausage, breaking it up.
Stir until pink color disappears; drain. Sprinkle flour and celery salt over sausage.
Heat and blend in tomatoes.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until slightly thickened.
Add drained beans.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Cover with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Can be frozen for cooking later.

title: wild summer salad
directions: Combine cooked, cooled rice with all ingredients. Toss lightly.
chill and serve.

title: blueberry-lemon cake with topping
directions: In a bowl, combine together flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in walnuts.
Set mixture aside.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Saute yellow onion, garlic and green onions in the olive oil until tender.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Pound breasts.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in flour mixture; brown in butter for 2 to 3 minutes per side.
Add the sauteed onions and garlic.
Over high heat, add sherry, lemon juice and capers.
This should thicken and make a nice gravy for the chicken.

title: south of the border bake
directions: Slice chicken into bite size pieces.
In skillet saute chicken in oil until cooked.
Divide chips, arranging one-half on bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Combine soup and salsa.
Fold in chicken. Spoon over chips.
Sprinkle cheese, top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In large bowl mix all ingredients well and serve.

title: sour cream cranberry salad
directions: Mix jellied cranberries and 1 cup hot water in blender or mixer until liquid and smooth.
Dissolve both packages of gelatin in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add cranberry mixture and pecans to gelatin.
Put half of the mixture in an 8-inch square pan and chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over top of chilled mixture. Add second half of gelatin over sour cream and refrigerate until firm.

title: snowballs
directions: Advance preparation:
Drain cherries well; let stand on paper toweling.
Combine butter or margarine, corn syrup and salt; stir in powdered sugar to make fondant.
Knead until smooth.
Chill. Shape about 1 teaspoon fondant mixture around each cherry.
Place on baking sheet lined with waxed paper; chill.

title: crisp watermelon rind pickles
directions: Prepare rind by removing all red and green.
Cut in desired shape.
Soak overnight in water and lime.
(You will need a large container for this.)

title: hearty onion and cheese soup
directions: Peel and slice onions 1/4-inch thick.
Separate into rings (onions should measure 4 cups).
Heat butter in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add onions and cook 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Stir in flour.
Add beef broth gradually.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Mash potatoes into broth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve with sliced crusty French bread. Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple and carrot salad
directions: Mix boiling water and jello in a bowl.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Add vinegar, pineapple and carrots to mixture. Garnish with walnuts if desired.
Chill until firm.

title: world's most delicious cookies (and they are!)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter and sugars; add egg and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time, except pecans.
Mix until all combined.
Stir in pecans.
Form dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten balls with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned; do not overcook.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Allow to cool slightly before removing from pan with spatula.

title: green chili pesto(sauce over pasta)
directions: In blender, puree all ingredients, except tomatoes, to make smooth sauce.
If necessary, thin slightly with water.

title: dump cake
directions: Spray 11x13 inch pan. Spread cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple into pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling and pineapple. Sprinkle nuts and coconut over cake mix. Pour melted margarine over this. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: portuguese roast
directions: Place roast, that has been seasoned with the spices and seasonings, in a large roaster pan.
Pour tomato sauce over roast. Cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Add chopped vegetables. Cut cabbage in large pieces.
Place on top of roast.
Cook for another 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: white cookies(sugar cookies)
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, vanilla and lemon extract.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and soda mixture.
Roll out to desired thickness.
(I roll to less than 1/4-inch thickness.)
Cut out circles or appropriate holiday shapes.
Bake at 375° until moderately golden brown.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Combine in bowl all except the chips.
Mix well.
Remove from bowl.
Knead until smooth.
Spread and pat into 9-inch square pan. Melt chips over low heat.
Spread over peanut butter mix.
Cool 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: deep fried pork
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on the chops.
Roll in flour and coat evenly.
Dip into mixture of egg.
Roll generously in bread crumbs.
Deep fry in oil (oil temperature should be 320° to 350°) to beautiful brown.

title: chow mein clusters
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt chocolate and butterscotch chips, stirring constantly, over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in noodles and nuts. Mix quickly, coating all noodles.
Dip out by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and cool.
You can substitute peanut butter chips for the butterscotch chips.

title: beer cheese
directions: Process in food processor and serve with crackers.

title: make ahead pineapple cream cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
In another bowl, add milk, pudding mix and cream cheese.
Beat until blended.
Put this mixture on top of cooled cake.
Cover with well drained, crushed pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 24 hours!
Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: crab dip
directions: Whip the cream cheese; add lemon and sherry, then crab.
Serve warm or cold.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat the olive oil in a large heavy skillet.
Saute the garlic and diced onions until the edges start to brown.
Add ground lamb and season with salt, pepper and rosemary leaves.
Brown the meat evenly, drain off grease and transfer meat to glass baking dish. Drain the can of corn and spread evenly over top of lamb.
Spread a layer of mashed potatoes 1 inch thick over top of meat and corn mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until potatoes brown around edges.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin in boiling water.

title: two minute white cake
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl and beat vigorously for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into two 8-inch layer pans lined on bottom with paper.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: seafoam lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add cold water and lemon juice. Slowly add to softened cream cheese; mix well.
Chill until almost firm.
Fold in nuts, marshmallows and pineapple.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.

title: polish coffee cake
directions: Pour into greased loaf pan; sprinkle streusel on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: lemon champagne punch
directions: Mix juices and water, chill.
Add ginger ale and sparkling water over ice.
Add champagne.
Serves 50.

title: vanilla cheesecake
directions: Finely roll 25 vanilla wafers.
Mix with 3 teaspoons sugar and margarine.
Press to bottom of spring-form pan.
Stand remaining wafers around the side of pan overlapping slightly.
With mixer, beat cream cheese and remaining sugar.
Blend in eggs, sour cream and orange juice and peel.
Spread into crust.
Bake at 350° until pie is set.
Let stand 1 hour after stove is turned off.
Chill. Serve.
Top with cranberry topping and garnish if desired.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Bring soups and onion to boil. Pour over rice and chicken in a dish. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
(Let stand.)
Beat eggs in oil and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in alternately with apple and sugar mixture.
Stir in walnuts. Pour in greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch) at 350° for 1/2 hour. Use any good cooking apples (Stayman apple is the best).

title: glazed gingered carrots
directions: Steam carrots until tender.
In frying pan, melt margarine. Add carrots and toss.
Sprinkle with sugar and ginger.
Mix lightly to coat carrots and continue cooking until carrots are lightly glazed, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Add parsley.

title: creamy mocha candies
directions: You will also need about 3 dozen (1-inch) foil candy cups.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Put milk, butter, sugar and salt in saucepan; heat until butter melts.
Set aside to cool to warm.
Mix yeast in the 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix yeast with milk mixture; stir in slightly beaten eggs. Add flour to make a dough you can knead.
Knead dough until smooth. Place dough in a greased bowl, turning over once to grease all sides of dough.
Cover and let rise about 1 hour, until double in bulk.

title: donnas buttermilk waffles
directions: Beat the eggs, buttermilk, then add the other ingredients. Then stir in melted butter.
Then put in the waffle iron.
Very light waffles.

title: crabmeat-eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant about 25 minutes.
Drain and mash.
Combine eggplant, onion, bell pepper, 1 cup bread crumbs, 1 1/2 cups cheese, salt and pepper and melted butter.
Mix until combined. Add crabmeat and beaten eggs.
Mix and pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread remaining cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Blend together the flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Mix together with first mixture. Roll in balls and roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line muffin tins with paper cupcake liners.
Beat the first 4 ingredients until well mixed.
Pour batter into tins and bake 40 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Mix together the sour cream, vanilla and 1/8 cup sugar.
Place a spoonful of white mixture in well formed on top of cake.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: quick seafood newburg
directions: Use any cooked seafood.
A mixture is great, but good old fake crabmeat is delicious.
Put into baking dish; sprinkle top with flour and add evaporated milk.
Season with salt, pepper and sherry.
Bake about 1/2 hour at 375° or until bubbly.
Serve with toast points.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Put in a 13 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden (15 to 20 minutes).
Cool.
Beat together 1 cup confectioners sugar, cream cheese and half of a 9 ounce carton of Cool Whip.
Mix well together and put over golden shell.
Beat together pudding and 4 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Top with remaining 1/2 of Cool Whip.

title: butter bean salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and add to cooked and drained butter beans.
Chill.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Set this aside.
Combine sugars and shortening, creaming well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
Add chopped nuts if desired.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly on cookie sheets.
Remove to rack and cool completely.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: apple pie
directions: In an unbaked pie shell, add the canned, drained apples.
Mix together the sugar, flour, salt, and cinnamon.
Put on top of the apples.

title: fresh banana cake or muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream shortening; slowly add sugar and beat until light. Add bananas, eggs and vanilla, beating well. Mix flour, baking soda and salt. Add to the first mixture and blend. Slowly add sour cream and beat until well blended. Spread into Bundt pan and bake 45 minutes. Cool in the pan 5 minutes before removing.

title: chili
directions: Brown and drain ground beef in Dutch oven.
Saute chopped onion in 1 teaspoon oil.
Combine seasonings, tomato sauce, water and chili beans (undrained).
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Blend dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat until smooth.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar, milk and flour together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook until firm at 375°.
Beat egg whites stiff; add 2 teaspoons sugar.
Spread on top of pie and lightly brown.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemon juice and milk. Chop fruit and drain. Add to Cool Whip mixture and mix well.
Put in 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown onion, garlic and beef in oil.
Add rest of ingredients. Cook uncovered 1 hour.
Cook 1 pound lasagne noodles 8 minutes. Rinse.
Place in large glass dish the noodles, sauce and cheese in layers.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: no-bake chocolate cheesecake
directions: Melt chocolate chips in top of a double boiler over hot, not boiling, water, stirring until smooth.
Combine cream cheese and sugar in a large mixer bowl; add margarine, beating until smooth. Blend in vanilla.
Beat in melted chocolate all at once.
Whip cream until stiff; fold into chocolate mixture.
Spoon into prepared graham cracker crust.
Chill thoroughly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then add following dressing about 4 hours before serving, chilled.

title: lynn's pork ribs
directions: Wash ribs, mix all seasonings together and pour over ribs. Cook on 275° for 2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add pecans, salt, vanilla and molasses.
Mix lightly but thoroughly. Pour into pie shell.

title: chicken stuffing bake
directions: Make stuffing, spoon in center of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange chicken on either side of stuffing.
Combine soup and milk in bowl.
Pour over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Uncover, bake 10 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: cheese soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine carrot, celery, onion and chicken broth.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Combine milk, flour and a dash of salt.
Stir into chicken broth mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered,
at 350° for 45 minutes.
Or after mixing, refrigerate overnight or until ready to bake, then bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix well and roll in chopped pecans.

title: sloppy joes for 75
directions: Cook beef and celery in 12-quart (or larger) kettle until beef loses redness; drain fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except hamburger buns) and blend well.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until desired consistency.
Serve on toasted or plain bun.
Makes about 75 (1/3 cup) servings.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook together for 20 minutes and seal.

title: easy dinner rolls
directions: Mix, with hand, one ingredient at a time.
Cover dough with a towel.
Let rise for 10 minutes, then punch down (knead 5 to 6 times).
Do this 6 times (every 10 minutes for 1 hour).
After last 10 minutes, punch (knead), pull off pinches of dough and roll in hand to form biscuit shape.

title: boiled coffee
directions: Combine and stir all the ingredients.
The egg shell
may be added to the mixture.
So may a pinch of salt.
Pour over these ingredients 4 cups freshly boiled water.
Boil the coffee for 3 or 4 minutes.
Stop the spout of the coffeepot with paper.
Set the pot on back of the stove.
Cut down the grounds from the sides and add 1/4 cup cold water and permit the coffee to stand for 10 minutes before serving it.

title: joggin juice
directions: Mix with mixer 5 minutes.
Drink 2 ounces per day.

title: all day shopping beef stew
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks. Mix all ingredients together in covered casserole dish.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours or at 300° for 3 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: tidewater on the halfshell
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash shrimp and spread in single layer in baking dish.
Mix all remaining ingredients except butter and pour over shrimp.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 20 minutes, stirring several times.
Serve in baking dish.
Use French bread for dipping into the sauce.
Serves 2.

title: melt-in-your mouth squash
directions: Wash and slice squash. Peel and dice onion. Spray skillet with Pam. Toss in vegetables
with the water that clings to them after washing. Salt and pepper to taste. Add sugar.
Cover and cook on medium-low for 15 to 20 minutes. Check occasionally to stir. Add water a tablespoon at a time as needed.

title: tostitos bean dip
directions: On a large platter, spread bean dip.
In a large bowl, peel and mash avocados with salt, pepper and lemon juice; spread on top of bean dip.

title: molded spinach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3/4 c. boiling water.
Add 1 c. cold water. Add vinegar, mayonnaise and salt.
Put in freezer tray & chill until firm 1 inch around sides of tray.
Turn into bowl and beat until fluffy, add celery, onion, spinach & cheese.
Place in 1 qt. mold and chill in refrigerator until firm.
Serves 6. Best if prepared a day before serving.

title: winter meeting drink
directions: Combine apple juice, water, honey and spices; bring to a boil. Simmer 30 minutes.
Let stand overnight.
Strain.
Add citrus to spiced apple drink.
Reheat but do not boil.
Serve.

title: plum cake
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar a little at a time.
Sift flour, cloves and cinnamon together and add to mixture.
Add plum baby food and oil.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.
Serves 4.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavorings.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool 10 or 15 minutes.
Turn onto wire rack.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Melt the butter. Add the cocoa. Stir until blended. Add the flour, vanilla, eggs and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Do not refrigerate.

title: banana split cake
directions: Bake cake as package directs.
Cool.
Poke holes all over cake.
Cook pineapple and sugar to boil, then simmer 20 minutes. Pour over cake.
Cool.
Prepare pudding as package directs; add cream cheese and whip together until light.
Spread over cake. Layer sliced bananas over cake, then spread Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and dot with cherries.
Cuts better if stored overnight.

title: chicken steaks
directions: Cut meat off bones; cut through meat to butterfly meat. Sprinkle seasoned salt and pepper.
Spray pan with oil; heat and fry chicken 3 to 4 minutes on each side until brown.
Serve with potatoes and salad.

title: children's applesauce dessert
directions: Place graham crackers in plastic bag and close tightly.
Child can use hands to crush graham crackers in bag.
Child can use spoon to scoop 1/3 applesauce into bowl.
Then another spoon to add 1/3 graham crackers to bowl.
Alternate layers until mixture is finished, ending with layer of graham crackers.

title: steamed rice
directions: Rinse the rice in a pan 3 to 4 times in cold water, draining most of the water off.
Place rice, water, oil and salt in a four-quart, nonstick saucepan.
Stir to mix well.
Bring to a boil, uncovered, then reduce heat to medium.
Let simmer until the rice is "au dent" and most of the water is absorbed.
Drain in a colander, discarding the water.

title: peppermint patties
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed mild and extract. Add 6 cups sugar: beat on low speed until smooth and well blended. Turn mixture onto surface sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Knead lightly to form smooth ball. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on wax paper-lined baking sheet. Flatten each ball in 1 1/2 inch patty. Chill for 2 hours. With fork, dip each patty into warm candy coating. Place on wax paper until firm.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed ingredients.
Stir in coconut, oatmeal, gumdrops, pecans and chocolate chips.
Form into balls; place on greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in a bread pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Pour 1/2 stick melted oleo over bread and bake another 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands.
Mold and chill.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix apples and sugar and let sit 10 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: aunt dorris' clothespin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add yolks and beat thoroughly.
Add flour and vanilla.
Roll in small balls.
Press a depression into top center of cookie with a wooden clothespin or thumb.
Fill depression with currant jelly or 1/2 pecan.
Bake until lightly browned at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tortellini salad with lemon-mustard vinaigrette
directions: Bring large pot of water to a boil. Meanwhile, place the lemon juice and zest in a large salad bowl. Whisk in the oil, mustard, dill, salt, black pepper, and sugar. Add the pasta to the boiling water and cook until al dente, 10 to 12 minutes, or according to package directions. Meanwhile, halve the cherry tomatoes. Cut the bell peppers into bite-sized pieces. Cut the zucchini into matchsticks. Cut the onion into thin rings. Finely chop the scallions. Drain the pasta and add it to the vinaigrette in the serving bowl. Add the vegetables and toss well to combine. Serve the salad warm or at room temperature.

title: sugared nuts
directions: In skillet, combine sugar, cinnamon and milk.
Cook to 236° (soft ball stage).
Stir in walnuts or pecan halves and vanilla extract.
Immediately turn out on wax paper and separate nuts (working quickly).
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: bran muffins
directions: Soak 1 cup cereal in 1 cup boiling water.
Cream together oleo, sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix flour, soda, salt and rest of cereal.

title: apple crisp
directions: Use enough apples to almost fill an 8-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and eggs until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples and top with cinnamon.
Melt 1/3 cup butter and pour over all.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked parsnips
directions: Boil parsnips until tender.
Cut in slices lengthwise.
Place in buttered baking dish and season with salt and pepper.
Pour melted butter or oleo over top and bake for 10 minutes.
Serve hot from baking dish.

title: finger steaks
directions: Tenderize steak; trim fat off.
Cut into strips (width and length of ring finger).
Mix seasoning with flour.
Roll steak in flour mixture, then dip in milk.
Roll in cornflake crumbs.
Deep fry in hot 375° oil for 3 to 5 minutes.
(The longer cooked the crumbs will become crispy.)
Dip in steak sauce.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl.
Cut in 1/2 of shortening until particles are the size of large beans.

Add the remaining shortening and cut until these particles are the size of peas. Sprinkle with water, mixing with fork until flour is moistened. Gather dough together with fingers so it cleans the bowl.
Press into ball.
Divide dough in half and shape each into a 6 to 8-inch circle.
Roll out about 1 inch larger than an inverted 9-inch pie pan.
Grease pie pan with shortening.
Ease bottom pastry into pan. Brush inside bottom crust with beaten egg.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add a small amount of water and simmer the squash and onion until tender.
Drain and add the chicken soup, salt and pepper to taste, sour cream and pimento.
Grease casserole and line bottom and sides with bread crumbs.
Heat 10 to 15 minutes in oven to brown top crumbs.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Keeps well refrigerated.

title: virginia spoon bread
directions: Mix meal, salt and shortening.
Scald with boiling water. Now, add beaten eggs, sweet milk and baking powder.
Mix well and pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in a 350` oven for 30 minutes or until it is springy.

title: easy indoor s'mores
directions: Place 5 cups miniature marshmallows, corn syrup, margarine and chocolate chips in large microwavable bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 2 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring after each minute until smooth and melted.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large bowl.
Mix quickly until completely coated.
Stir in 1 cup miniature marshmallows.
Press into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain beans and peas in colander.
Combine all ingredients and marinate overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator several weeks.

title: mama's banana pudding
directions: Mix
together
in saucepan on medium heat the sugar and add flour.
Stir
thoroughly.
Add
milk.
Save
1/4 cup milk with egg yolks.
Beat thoroughly.
Add dash of salt.
Stirring slowly,
add margarine.
Cook
until
thickens.
Add vanilla. Layer in baking dish beginning with pudding, layer of bananas, layer of
vanilla wafers
on top.
Top with beaten egg whites and brown in oven at 325° until golden brown.

title: aunt gladys' blueberry muffins
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl (butter can be a little lumpy).
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pickle relish
directions: Mix cucumbers and onions.
Add salt and let set 2 hours, then drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat altogether, put in jars and seal.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine sugar, salt, shortening and hot water in a large bowl. Cool to lukewarm. Soften the yeast in warm water.
Add yeast, beaten egg and half the flour. Beat well. Stir in rest of flour and mix thoroughly.
Place in a greased bowl. Grease top. Cover and place in refrigerator overnight or until ready to use.
Punch down. Cut off dough and shape into rolls.
Let rise until double in size. Bake in greased pan at 425° for
20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: corn bread
directions: Pour oil to cover bottom of a 10 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet and preheat in a 425° oven.
Mix ingredients well and pour into hot skillet.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine broth, broccoli and onion. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in milk and cream of mushroom soup.
Heat until hot, do not boil.

title: nora's meat loaf
directions: Chop onion, bell pepper and saltines up real fine.
Add egg, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Stir together.
Mix with hamburger until you form a dough that pulls away from sides of the bowl.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Wash peppers and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove veins and seeds.
Cut in lengthwise strips and pack in hot, sterilized pint jars.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain off water.

title: toffee
directions: In 2 to 3-quart saucepan, melt butter (use butter, doesn't burn as easy as margarine).
Add sugar and lecithin.
Stir constantly with wooden spoon.
Cook over medium to high heat until mixture comes to boil.
Add syrup.
Cook to 305°.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
(I use Pam.)
While hot, top with milk chocolate chips; spread evenly over the top and top with nuts.
When cool, break into pieces or may be scored while warm.
Very good.

title: punch (for 100 people)
directions: Make a syrup of sugar and water by bringing to a boil.
Pour all juices into a large container and add syrup.
Cool.
Add ginger ale before serving.
Pour over ice.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, flour and dry Jell-O.
Add oil, water and strawberries.
Blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Bake in 3-layer pans, greased and floured, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding beaten egg whites last.
Bake in 2 square pans or 3 (9-inch) round pans in a 350° to 375° oven until straw comes out clean.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Pour milk over bread cubes and let stand.
Cream eggs, sugar and butter.
Mix with bread mixture.
Add pineapple (don't drain). Mix lightly and bake in uncovered casserole for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serves 8 to 10.
A great side dish with ham.
Can be served hot or cold.
A sprinkle of cinnamon is an added touch.

title: smothered steak
directions: Salt and pepper tenderized steaks.
Flour and brown steaks in hot oil. Remove steaks and drain excess oil. Add flour left in skillet and brown.
Saute onion in this mixture.
Add water and/or beer. Stir until smooth. Add steaks and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Season to taste, the mixture.

title: sausage, sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Form 6 sausage patties and brown in hot skillet. Drain off part of the fat.
Core apples (not cutting through end and do not peel).
Fill centers with brown
sugar and butter.
Place apples and peeled sweet potatoes over sausage.
Add water and salt. Cover skillet and bring mixture to
a boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Uncover and glaze under broiler. Serves 4.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Add bay leaves and simmer for 3 hours or until tender.
Skim fat off water.
Remove from bone and dice.
Add a little stock to flour and make a smooth paste.
Blend into rest of stock.
Add vegetables, except parsley, and cook slowly.
When finished, add chicken and parsley.
Divide filling into individual dishes.
Top each with baked crust before serving. Serves 12.

title: liz's shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add shrimp, turning every few minutes to cook.
Add rest of ingredients, except bread crumbs. Cover with lid and simmer a few more minutes.
Add bread crumbs to make a sauce.
Add according to the desired thickness of sauce. Stir everything to mix well.
Serve with rice and vegetables.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Put oats and raisins in bowl.
Add boiling water; set aside. Mix all remaining ingredients in large bowl except flour.
Add oatmeal and raisins, then add flour; mix well.
Bake in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Men love this cake!

title: creamy fettuccini alfredo
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat until bubbly and well mixed.
Add garlic powder.
Add fettuccini and mix well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook onion in oil until tender, but not browned.
Stir in chicken broth, tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, salt and pepper. Heat to boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add basil and simmer for 5 minutes longer.
Cool slightly.
Put small amounts of tomato soup in a blender or food processor.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directions on box. Also mix in the ingredients. Let set slightly.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix jello, water and 7-Up.
Let cool until partially set, then add drained pineapple (save juice), diced bananas and marshmallows. Let set until firm.
Mix sugar, flour, egg, juice and water.
Cook until thick, then cool.
Whip Dream Whip and combine with the cooked mixture.
Spread over top of salad.
Chill until ready to serve.
Use a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: t's macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat water and add bouillon cubes.
When water boils, add macaroni.
Cook according to package directions.
Drain well.
Cut ham into small strips.
Place a layer of pasta over bottom of lightly greased pan.
Sprinkle with layer of ham.
Continue layers until all is used.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Add together sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Make a well and add coconut, nuts, bananas, crushed pineapple, vanilla, oil or corn oil and eggs.
Stir to blend well the remaining ingredients.
Do not beat.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325°.
Do not open oven door until cake has baked 1 hour, then begin testing for doneness with a toothpick:
1 hour and 20 minutes, tube cake and 1 hour and 5 minutes, loaf pan.

title: hot pecan dip
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Fold in the sour cream. Spoon into shallow pan.
Top with pecans or walnuts (chopped), which have been browned in margarine.
Add a sprinkle of basil and sesame seed to nut topping.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: mamaw's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool.
Can be frozen.

title: fabric ribbon
directions: Measure 1/2 cup glossy laundry starch granules and mix with 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir constantly.
Cool.
Add 1 tablespoon white glue per cup of starch.
Saturate the fabric and lay out to dry or hang up.
When dry, steam press and cut to desired width.

title: egg roll(lumpia)
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients except for egg roll wrappers and oil for frying.
Take a heaping tablespoonful and roll in egg roll wrapper.
Make a long roll about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Deep fat fry.
Serve with soy sauce or sweet and sour sauce.

title: cassia bud pickles
directions: Cut lengthwise 75 two to three-inch cucumbers.
Heat to boiling 4 quarts water and 2 cups coarse salt; cool and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 1 week.
Drain; cover with boiling water and let stand 24 hours.
Drain; cover with hot syrup made with 6 cups vinegar, 5 cups sugar, 1 ounce celery seed and one ounce cassia buds.
For 3 consecutive days, drain off syrup into stainless steel pot; add 1 cup sugar and heat to boiling.
Pour over pickles.
On third day, drain; put cucumbers into sterile jars. Pour over hot syrup.
Seal.
Process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 14 pints.

title: relish salad
directions: Bring to a boil the oil, vinegar, water, salt and pepper.
In large bowl put corn, peas, green beans, green onions, carrots and celery.
Pour boiled mixture in bowl with vegetables.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: coke salad
directions: In a pan crumble cheese; add juice of pineapple and cherries. Heat until cheese is melted.
Pour over jello.
Then add fruit and nuts.
Add 14 ounces of Coke.
Pour into molds or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Cut into squares.
(Add cake coloring, if desired, before chilling.)

title: microwave layered fiesta spread
directions: In a 10-inch microwave-safe pie plate, combine onion and ground beef.
Cover with waxed paper and cook on High for 5 to 8 minutes until meat is done and onion is tender, stirring once. Drain off fat.
Stir in chili powder and beans.
Cook, covered, on High for 4 to 6 minutes until heated through; stir once.
Spread avocado dip over meat mixture and cook, uncovered, on High for 3 to 4 minutes until hot.
Give dish half turn once.
Top with shredded cheese.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 to 2 minutes until cheese is softened.
Spoon sour cream over the cheese and serve with tortilla chips.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add egg, salad oil and milk.
Beat all together until well mixed.
Add blueberries; fold over until mixed.
Fill greased muffin tins half full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chow-chow
directions: Grind
hot
and
sweet	peppers,
onions,
tomatoes and cabbage.
Cover hot and sweet peppers with boiling water.
Let stand 15
minutes.	Drain.	Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Cook 30 minutes and seal in airtight jars.

title: alphabet casserole
directions: Add soup to browned meat and onion.
Add tomatoes and noodles. Stir to mix.
Pour into a buttered 1-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and add the rhubarb.
Mix until well blended and pour into a 9 inch pie shell.
Cover with top crust and bake 10 minutes at 425 degrees and then turn down to 350 degrees for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: coffee brickle ice cream
directions: In small bowl, dissolve coffee in water.
In ice cream freezer containers, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Freeze leftovers.

title: carne guasado
directions: Trim fat from meat and cut into strips approximately 1/2-inch wide and 3 to 4 inches long.
In a large skillet heat enough oil to lightly coat bottom; brown meat with onions.
When lightly browned, remove meat; to meat drippings add enough flour to make gravy.
Stir water in slowly and stir constantly until gravy is a nice consistency.
Add all remaining ingredients, meat and onions; bring to a boil and then reduce heat to simmer.
Let simmer for 45 minutes to one hour (or until meat is very
tender).
Serve with warm flour tortillas and refried beans.

title: lemon chicken-n-potatoes
directions: Pierce potatoes with fork and microwave on High 6 minutes. Let stand 2 minutes; cut into 1/2-inch chunks and set aside. Spray a large nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray. Add oil and place over medium-high heat until hot. Place potatoes in skillet, cut sides down. Cook 6 minutes or until cooked through and golden brown, turning occasionally. Stir in onions, 1 tablespoon lemon peel and basil. Cook 2 minutes, stirring often. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Remove from skillet and keep warm. Spray skillet again with vegetable cooking spray. Heat over medium heat. Add chicken; cook about 10 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and juices run clear, turning once. Increase heat to medium-high. Stir in broth, scraping up any bits on bottom of pan. Stir in parsley and remaining 2 tablespoons lemon juice and 1 tablespoon lemon peel. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Return potatoes to skillet; toss to heat through. Serve with buttered French bread, sliced steamed vegetables and deep dish peaches-n-cream pie.

title: quick and easy pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Can use for diabetics if you use all nonsugar products.
If not sweet enough to suit taste, add a little Sweet 'N Low or other sugar substitute.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Great topped with pecans.
Makes 1 pie.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Clean and dry thoroughly 2 pounds of fresh cranberries.
Freeze overnight.
Grind cranberries without thawing.
Squeeze the juice from 2 oranges and then grind the rind.
Mix altogether with sugar substitute to taste.
Yield:
4 cups.
Carbohydrate 2 g, protein 0 g, fat 0 g, calories 8. One tablespoon = free food exchange.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Bake pie crust according to instructions.
Mix eggs, cream, salt and pepper together.
Place broccoli, onion, mushrooms and cheeses in pie crust.
Pour egg and cream mixture over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour and golden brown.

title: mini ham and cheese rolls
directions: Slice rolls through center.
Layer with ham and cheese. Replace rolls in foil tray.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Pour over rolls; leave uncovered, until butter sets, then cover.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: If mushroom are very small, leave whole. If not, slice thinly. Crush and peel garlic and cut into slivers. Mix mushrooms, olive oil, lemon juice, marjoram, garlic and pepper together. Let sit for 2 hours or overnight to marinate. Serve as part of an antipasto platter. Serves 6.

title: easy stuffed cabbage
directions: Take ground chuck and raw rice; mix together with parsley, dill and garlic powder.
Layer cabbage leaves on bottom and sides of a roaster.
Then add a layer of ground chuck mixture.
Repeat cabbage leaves and ground meat mixture.
Add 1 large can of tomato sauce and large can of tomatoes and 1 cup of water.
Add enough liquid to keep it moist.
Bake at 325° for about 2 1/2 hours.

title: cashew mayonnaise
directions: Blend
all ingredients smooth.
Cook until thick.
Stir in 1/4 cup lemon juice.
Chill and serve.
Makes approximately 1 1/4 cups.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix well the cream cheese and mayonnaise with electric mixer. Add milk, salt, hot sauce and garlic powder.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Taste mixture.
Add more hot sauce or garlic powder if desired.
Stir in crab meat.
Use canned or fresh meat. Fresh crab is best, but canned is also delicious.
Serve with crackers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Roll biscuits in sugar mixture and layer in pan.
After all biscuits are layered, take leftover sugar mixture and pour back into cup.
Add enough brown sugar to make a full cup of sugar.
Take 1/2 cup margarine and sugar and cook until smooth.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Shred cucumbers and press out excess moisture.
Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Chill. Serve as sandwich spread.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place brisket, fat side up, in roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 450°.
Remove from oven.
Cover generously, in this order, with garlic powder, pepper, paprika, instant coffee, carrot, onion, parsley and bouillon cubes (dissolved in juice). Cover pan.
Return to oven; bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours, or until tender, basting occasionally.
Remove from oven; refrigerate overnight.
Slice meat across the grain.
Return to pan with juices.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saut bacon and onion over medium heat. In saucepan, add potatoes, salt, pepper, water, bacon and onions. Cook until potatoes are tender. Add clams, 1 cup clam liquid, cream and butter. Simmer 10 minutes. Stir frequently.

title: herb bread
directions: Let bread rise according to directions.
Blend all ingredients together.
Grease bottom of cookie sheet.
Pull bread apart and form into 3-inch pieces.
Butter each piece and place one after another to form a loaf.
Makes 2.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well.
Grease and flour four (1-pound) coffee cans.
Fill 1/2 full, bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: manwell scottish shortbread
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add 1/2 of the flour and beat another 2 to 4 minutes until fluffy.
Add remainder of flour and work into dough with hands until blended.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Crimp edges and prick all over with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until delicately brown.
Cool slightly and cut into small squares.

title: green 'n salad
directions: Layer as follows:
lettuce, green onions, celery, green peppers, green peas, Salad Supreme spice, bacon, mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: yuksobi
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Rinse fat; add 1 cup water and bring to a boil.
Add vegetables, lower heat and simmer until tender.
Cook Ramen noodles in a separate pan.
Follow package directions.
Serves 12.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Combine 1 stick margarine, 1/4 cup cocoa and 1 cup water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; mix well.
Pour over mixture of flour, sugar and salt in bowl.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk, eggs, soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: hobo bread
directions: Soak raisins in water and add soda. Stir and cover.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, add sugar, salt and oil.
Add flour, one cup at a time, stirring well after each cup.
Grease and flour 3 soup cans (1/2 batch).
Fill half full and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate.
Good for country ribs over low heat in electric skillet.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crumble crackers and mix all the ingredients by hand very well. If it doesn't seem moist enough, wet hands. Do not add more water. Pack into loaf pan lined with wax paper. Store in refrigerator and enjoy.

title: mama's old fashioned caramel pie
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients all together and heat well (not boiling) on the stove, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and set aside.

title: barbecued sandwiches
directions: Brown meat (you can substitute ground beef with ground turkey).
Add other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: quesadillas
directions: Spread whole tortilla with layer of beans and grated cheese. Top with another tortilla.
In skillet with oil, brown on both sides until cheese is melted.
Top with picante sauce, if desired. Make as many as you like.
Cut into fourths before serving.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix in large bowl until all ingredients are well mixed.
Place in deep pan.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients; combine liquids.
Add all at once and stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Batter should not be smooth but somewhat lumpy. Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: red snapper fillet
directions: For six generous servings, buy 6 pounds of your favorite style ribs and cut in strips of three.
Using an earthenware or glass dish (not metal), soak overnight in Marinade.

title: broccoli-rice deluxe
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Combine next six ingredients.
Pour in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Add cheese; let melt in oven.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream
margarine
to
consistency
of
mayo.
Add sugar while continuing	to cream.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat until light. Add
flour,
baking
powder and salt; blend in.
Chill several hours or until firm enough to roll.
Cut out.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes (do not overbake).

title: finger paint
directions: Mix flour and salt. Add cold water. Beat until smooth and gradually add hot water. Boil until clear. Beat until smooth. Add food coloring.
Store in jars in the refrigerator.

title: yogurt mint drink
directions: Use can of yogurt and 1 pitcher of water.
Add lots of mint with cucumbers and salt.
Stir well.

title: taco salad
directions: Tortilla Bowls:
Put the lid of a 10-inch skillet on top of 8 sheets of foil.
Draw a circle and cut out.
Warm tortillas until pliable.
Put 2 foil circles together.
Top with warm tortilla. Shape tortilla and foil together into a ruffled bowl and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak the instant onions in water.
Brown bacon; drain and crumble.
Mix all the ingredients except onion rings together in a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, covered.
Add one can of onion rings on top for the last half hour of cooking and bake, uncovered.

title: mixed salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with just enough salad dressing to cover fruit.

title: hush puppies
directions: Drop from spoon and fry in deep hot fat.

title: brown sugar bars
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Melt margarine in a saucepan large enough to serve as a mixing bowl.
Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well. Add nuts.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: crab lasagne
directions: Start at 3:00 p.m. for 6:00 dinner.
Preheat oven to 400°. Place roast in oven and bake for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and keep oven door closed.
Forty-five minutes before serving, turn oven to 325° (5:15 p.m.).

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add raisins and rice.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Add nutmeg on top.
Set in pan of water and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat eggs and flour until creamy.
Combine cocoa, butter, flour, vanilla and coconut.
Mix and add to egg mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread with Marshmallow Creme.
Let set and spread with frosting.

title: chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cube chicken breasts and cook in electric skillet with small amount of oil.
Mix chicken, noodles, soup and milk together.
Pour in casserole pan sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle Pepperidge Farm stuffing on top with 1 1/2 tablespoons margarine; pepper to taste.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: stewed corn
directions: Cut corn close to outer edge; then scrape ear to remove all the milk.
Melt margarine in a heavy skillet; add corn and then other ingredients.
Stir frequently.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes.
More margarine may be added during the final minutes of cooking.

title: island treasure cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda; set aside. In medium mixing bowl, beat butter, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Add egg; mix well.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in coconut, Macadamia nuts and milk chocolate chips.

title: macaroni and vegetable salad
directions: Add all ingredients; toss lightly.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit delight
directions: Spray 8 inch square pan.
Put 1 can Pie Filling (peach, apple etc.) into bottom of pan then top with flour mixture.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Add small cut mushrooms pieces to hamburger.
Add onion and garlic.
Brown hamburger mixture and drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 1 hour for spaghetti and coney wieners. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: gingerbread cookies(rolled)
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add the egg and mix well.
Add the flour, salt, soda, baking powder, ginger, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix thoroughly. Store dough at least 2 hours in refrigerator before rolling on floured board and cutting into cookies.
Roll at least 1/4-inch thick. Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.
Use an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: pull-a-part bread
directions: Heat milk to
boiling,	pour
over
margarine, salt and sugar. Use a large
bowl	for
this, stir until dissolved and cool to lukewarm.
Add
yeast, dissolved in lukewarm water and slightly beaten egg.
Mix
well.
Stir
in
flour gradually to make a soft dough.
Let
rise
until
double
(about
1 hour). Knead
lightly and
roll
to
1/3-inch
thickness	on
floured surface.
Spread on melted margarine.
Cut into slices about 2 x 3 1/2-inches. Place
these
in bread pan (standing on edge) which has been greased, butter sides touching.
Let rise again and bake about 30 minutes
in 350° oven.
Makes one large or 2 small loaves.	Dough can also be used for cinnamon rolls or as plain ones.

title: poppycock
directions: Mix together popped corn and nuts on large cookie sheet.
In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, butter and Karo syrup.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling and stirring until mixture turns a medium caramel color (290°, hard crack).
Remove from heat.
Add 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour over corn and nuts; mix to coat well.
Spread out to dry.

title: chicken casserole(crock-pot)
directions: Boil chicken first, then cook noodles in broth.
After noodles are done, add other ingredients and serve out of crock-pot.
Real good.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients. Store covered in refrigerator. Use with cooked, peeled shrimp.

title: chocolate chip date nut cake
directions: Combine dates, boiling water and soda.
Let soak.
Combine sugar, margarine and eggs in mixer and blend well.
Drain liquid off dates and add liquid to sugar and egg mixture, alternating with flour and salt.
Stir dates in last.
Pour in 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped nuts over batter followed by a sprinkling of granulated sugar.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cut in small squares or cut larger squares and top with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, onion & 2/3 of cheese. Roll in tortillas. Put in pan. Mix soup & green chilies & heat; then add sour cream & heat thoroughly. Pour over tortillas, then add remaining cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg, then the sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake immediately in hot waffle iron.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole (2)
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13 in. baking dish.
Bake at 350°F for 1 hr.

title: miniature biscuits
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Grease muffin pans.
Drop by spoonfuls in pan.
Bake about 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 36 biscuits.

title: low-fat chicken broth
directions: In a large kettle, combine all ingredients.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Remove chicken and remove meat from bones.
Discard the vegetables.
Strain the broth and refrigerate stock overnight. The fat will rise to the top.
Skim off fat.
Use the broth and meat for soup or freeze broth in ice cube trays.
Store in plastic Ziploc bags in freezer.
Use cubes as needed to saute in place of oil or to add as needed to soups, stews, etc.

title: fritter batter for "hot dogs"
directions: Stir dry ingredients and add well beaten eggs and milk.
The batter should be just thick enough to cover the hot dog.
If it is too thin, add more flour.
If it is too thick, add more milk. Place a wooden stick in each hot dog.
Deep fry in hot oil.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix as any other cake.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and buttermilk.
Mix flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.
Bake at 350° or a little less until done, but not brown.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese; mix sausage, cheese and biscuit mix.
Roll in hands to form balls.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Thinly slice potatoes. Keep in cold water until used. Melt butter in 1-quart saucepan. Add flour, salt and pepper. Blend. Add milk. Stir constantly and bring almost to a boil; it will be thickened. Drain potatoes and add to sauce, stirring to coat. Place in shallow pan or casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Recipe can be doubled.

title: dough christmas ornaments
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate and then use to make whatever kind of ornament.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes to 1 hour.
The baking time depends on how thick the ornaments are.
Do not let them get brown!

title: tutti fruiti ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add milk to fill freezer to 3/4 full.
Freeze.
Yields 1 1/2 gallons.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift together baking powder, baking soda, sugar, salt, corn meal and flour, then add egg, milk and oil and beat by hand until smooth.
Bake in an 8-inch square pan or muffin pans in a preheated 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 14 corn sticks. Pour cornbread batter into hot, well-greased corn stick pans. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and cranberry juice.
Mix well. Add lemon juice and salt.
Chill mixture to mound at jiggly stage (don't let jello get stiff).
Beat jello mixture with a beater. Add mayonnaise.
Beat.
Stir in cranberries, apples and nuts by hand.
Place in a mold and chill. Can use cooked dressing for the 1 cup mayonnaise.

title: baked vegetables
directions: Cut all vegetables into large pieces.
Sprinkle lightly with salt; top with oleo.
Mix all vegetables together.
Put into heavy foil and close tight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Do not open foil or add any liquid.
Makes its own.

title: english peas and green bean salad
directions: Drain green beans and English peas well.
Add celery and onion.
Marinate for 24 hours in sugar, vinegar, vegetable oil, water and salt and pepper.
Keep refrigerated.
Keeps for days. Drain before serving.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer twice, starting with lettuce, etc and ending with sugar. Let stand 6 hours or overnight.
Next day, mix all together.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the beans, then pour mixture over the combined beans.
Marinate in the refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Will keep in the refrigerator 2 weeks.

title: vanilla pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, two at a time.
Add flour and vanilla; beat until well mixed.
Pour into a greased and floured angel food cake pan or 3 loaf pans.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Boil sugar and water until syrup reaches the soft ball stage when dropped in cold water.
Add the butter and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Let cool, then beat until thick and creamy.
Add cream until it spreads easy.
Enough frosting for 2 (9-inch) cakes.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Wash shrimp and place in 1-quart boiling water.
Bring water back to boiling.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Remove shrimp and add next 5 ingredients to cooking water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Peel, devein and chop shrimp.
When stock is finished simmering, blend in blender with 1/2 the shrimp until smooth.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat eggs and add to the milk.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix and pour through a funnel into deep hot oil.
Funnel opening should be about 5/8-inch wide.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake on a greased and floured large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peach kuchen(german peach cake)
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients; pat into an 8-inch pie pan.
Peel and slice peaches.
Mix peaches with cornstarch and lemon juice.
Pour peach filling onto crust.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until fruit is tender.
Double amounts for roasting pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and cook 1 cup juice with pudding mix.
(Do not add milk or water.)
Chill and add fruit.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut cooked chicken into small pieces and place in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix soups, almonds and sour cream, sprinkle with garlic salt and poppy seeds.
Pour over chicken, add top crust and bake at 350 degrees until bubbly.

title: dixie waffles
directions: Sift all the dry ingredients together twice.
Mix liquid ingredients; combine with the dry.
Bake on hot, well greased waffle iron and serve with maple syrup.
Makes 6 good size Dixie Waffles.

title: welsh tea cakes
directions: Scald currants to soften and drain.
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture is mealy.
Add egg, milk and currants.
Mix until all ingredients are moist and dough holds together.
Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut with cookie cutter.
Heat griddle or electric frypan (about 350° to 375°).
Grease lightly.
Place cookies on griddle.
When brown on bottom, turn and brown other side.
After removing from griddle, sprinkle with sugar.

title: pesto pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Add other ingredients and serve!

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Add milk and other ingredients. Cook over medium heat approximately 7 minutes until smooth and thick.

title: pineapple and cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save 3 tablespoons juice; arrange pineapple on the bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir together flour and sugar; sprinkle over pineapple.
Drizzle pineapple juice over top with cheese.
Mix crushed crackers and butter.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered. Uncover and bake for 10 minutes.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Mix the sour cream, 3/4 cup sugar and flour.
Slice the apples; toss sliced apples in sour cream mixture.
Pour into a pie crust.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon; dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, until apples are cooked.

title: kids party punch
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: *Use ginger ale or water to make 1 cup.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Layer brownies, pudding, Heath bars, caramel and Cool Whip. Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: sticky grahams
directions: Boil butter and brown sugar.
Place graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Pour mixture over, then sprinkle pecans on.
Cool and pull up.

title: tuna tetrazzini
directions: In a 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish, melt butter or margarine on High 40 seconds.
Stir in flour, then cream, bouillon, wine and seasoned salt.
Stirring twice, cook on High 5 minutes.
Fold in Cheddar cheese, green onions, mushrooms, tuna and cooked, drained spaghetti.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook on High 3 to 4 minutes. Garnish with chopped parsley.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine and pack in bottom of pan.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: In large bowl, combine milk, cranberries, pineapple and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: brownies
directions: Combine melted chocolate with shortening and blend well. Sift flour and baking powder together.
Beat eggs and add sugar, gradually, beating until very light.
Add vanilla next, then the chocolate mixture.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Blend well. Spread 1/2-inch deep in greased shallow pan.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough. Put in greased bowl.
Put in icebox.
Will keep for several days. Make out rolls and set in warm place about 2 hours before baking. Will rise to about double in size.
Bake in hot oven.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions, using above ingredients, water, skim milk and diet margarine.
Omit salt called for on package.
Set aside.

title: ann lander's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat thoroughly.
Pat into loaf pan. Cover with 2 strips bacon (optional).
Pour 8 ounce can tomato sauce over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
